WEBVTT

00:00:18.680 --> 00:00:24.440
The Proverbs of Solomon, the son of David,

00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:32.200
King of Israel, to know wisdom and instruction, to perceive the words of understanding,

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:38.520
to perceive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment and equity,

00:00:39.160 --> 00:00:44.760
to give subtlety to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion.

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:52.660
A wise man will hear and will increase learning, and a man of understanding shall attain unto

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:59.660
wise counsels, to understand a proverb and the interpretation, the words of the wise,

00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:09.160
and their dark sayings. The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge, but fools despise

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:16.500
wisdom and instruction. My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:23.880
mother, for they shall be an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck.

00:01:24.600 --> 00:01:35.000
My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not. If they say, Come with us, let us lay

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:42.380
wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause, let us swallow them

00:01:42.380 --> 00:01:51.080
alive as the grave, and whole as those that go down into the pit, we shall find all precious

00:01:51.080 --> 00:02:00.500
substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil. Cast in thy lot among us, let us all have one purse.

00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:09.320
My son, walk not thou in the way with them, refrain thy foot from their path, for their

00:02:09.320 --> 00:02:17.400
run to evil, and make haste to shed blood, surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird,

00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:25.180
and they lay wait for their own blood, they lurk privily for their own lives.

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:32.960
So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain, which taketh away the life of the owners

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:42.520
thereof. Wisdom crieth without, she uttereth her voice in the streets, she crieth in the chief

00:02:42.520 --> 00:02:50.180
place of concourse, in the openings of the gates, in the city she uttereth her words, saying,

00:02:50.980 --> 00:02:58.480
How long ye simple ones will ye love simplicity, and the scorners delight in their scorning,

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:07.770
and fools hate knowledge. Turn you at my reproof, behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you,

00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:15.340
I will make known my words unto you, because I have called and ye refused, I have stretched

00:03:15.340 --> 00:03:28.460
out my hand, and no man regarded, but ye have said at nought all my counsel, and would none of my

00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:36.720
when your fear cometh, when your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a

00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:44.300
whirlwind, when distress and anguish cometh upon you, then shall they call upon me, but I will

00:03:44.300 --> 00:03:52.380
not answer, they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me, for that they hated knowledge,

00:03:52.380 --> 00:04:00.860
and did not choose the fear of the Lord, they would none of my counsel, they despised all my

00:04:00.860 --> 00:04:09.580
reproof, therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices,

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:18.400
for the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them,

00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:26.720
but whoso hearkeneth unto me, shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.

00:04:38.335 --> 00:04:39.475
II.

00:04:51.255 --> 00:04:58.655
My son, if thou wilt receive my words, and hide my commandments with thee, so that thou

00:04:58.655 --> 00:05:06.195
incline thine ear unto wisdom, and apply thine heart to understanding, yea, if thou cryest

00:05:06.195 --> 00:05:12.875
after knowledge, and liftest up thy voice for understanding, if thou seekest her as

00:05:12.875 --> 00:05:19.675
silver and searchest for her as for hid treasures, then shalt thou understand the fear of the

00:05:19.675 --> 00:05:23.175
Lord, and find the knowledge of God.

00:05:23.655 --> 00:05:29.435
For the Lord giveth wisdom, out of his mouth cometh knowledge and understanding, he layeth

00:05:29.435 --> 00:05:37.955
for the righteous, he is a buckler to them that walk uprightly, he keepeth the paths of

00:05:37.955 --> 00:05:41.595
judgment and preserveth the way of his saints.

00:05:42.555 --> 00:05:49.355
Then shalt thou understand righteousness, and judgment, and equity, yea, every good path.

00:05:49.935 --> 00:05:56.635
When wisdom entereth into thine heart, and knowledge is pleasant unto thy soul, discretion

00:05:56.635 --> 00:06:02.895
shall preserve thee, understanding shall keep thee, to deliver thee from the way of the

00:06:02.895 --> 00:06:11.255
evil man, from the man that speaketh foward things, who leave the paths of uprightness

00:06:11.255 --> 00:06:18.475
to walk in the ways of darkness, who rejoice to do evil, and delight in the fowardness

00:06:18.475 --> 00:06:25.595
of the wicked, whose ways are crooked, and they foward in their paths, to deliver thee

00:06:25.595 --> 00:06:32.235
from the strange woman, even from the stranger which flattereth with her words, which forsaketh

00:06:32.235 --> 00:06:39.295
the guide of her youth, and forgetteth the covenant of her God, for her house inclineth

00:06:39.295 --> 00:06:47.495
unto death, and her paths unto the dead, none that go unto her return again, neither take

00:06:47.495 --> 00:06:54.235
they hold of the paths of life, that thou mayest walk in the way of good men, and keep the

00:06:54.235 --> 00:06:59.955
paths of the righteous, for the upright shall dwell in the land, and the perfect shall remain

00:06:59.955 --> 00:07:07.575
in it, but the wicked shall be cut off from the earth, and the transgressors shall be

00:07:07.575 --> 00:07:08.815
rooted out of it.

00:07:30.848 --> 00:07:35.848
My son, forget not my law, but let thine heart keep my commandments.

00:07:36.508 --> 00:07:41.288
For length of days, and long life, and peace shall they add to thee.

00:07:41.948 --> 00:07:44.288
Let not mercy and truth forsake thee.

00:07:44.668 --> 00:07:46.348
Bind them about thy neck.

00:07:46.348 --> 00:07:49.068
Write them upon the table of thine heart.

00:07:49.948 --> 00:07:54.908
So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man.

00:07:55.788 --> 00:08:02.168
Trust in the Lord with all thine heart, and lean not unto thine own understanding.

00:08:03.128 --> 00:08:08.388
In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.

00:08:09.108 --> 00:08:14.728
Be not wise in thine own eyes, fear the Lord, and depart from evil.

00:08:14.728 --> 00:08:19.668
He shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones.

00:08:20.708 --> 00:08:25.988
Honour the Lord with thy substance, and with the first fruits of all thine increase.

00:08:26.468 --> 00:08:33.868
So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.

00:08:34.688 --> 00:08:40.988
My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord, neither be weary of his correction.

00:08:40.988 --> 00:08:48.408
For whom the Lord loveth, he correcteth, even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.

00:08:49.208 --> 00:08:54.868
Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that geteth understanding.

00:08:56.188 --> 00:09:00.268
For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver,

00:09:00.668 --> 00:09:03.208
and the gain thereof than fine gold.

00:09:03.748 --> 00:09:10.608
She is more precious than rubies, and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.

00:09:10.608 --> 00:09:17.728
Length of days is in her right hand, and in her left hand riches and honour.

00:09:18.208 --> 00:09:23.628
Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.

00:09:24.648 --> 00:09:31.508
She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her, and happy is every one that retaineth her.

00:09:32.188 --> 00:09:39.588
The Lord by wisdom hath founded the earth, by understanding hath he established the heavens.

00:09:39.588 --> 00:09:46.028
By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.

00:09:46.928 --> 00:09:53.848
My son, let not them depart from thine eyes, keep sound wisdom and discretion.

00:09:54.448 --> 00:09:58.968
So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.

00:09:59.548 --> 00:10:04.828
Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.

00:10:04.828 --> 00:10:12.128
When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid, yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.

00:10:13.648 --> 00:10:20.048
Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.

00:10:20.368 --> 00:10:25.768
For the Lord shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.

00:10:26.788 --> 00:10:32.208
Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it.

00:10:32.208 --> 00:10:40.108
Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and tomorrow I will give, when thou hast it by thee.

00:10:40.908 --> 00:10:46.868
Divise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.

00:10:47.388 --> 00:10:52.568
Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.

00:10:53.268 --> 00:10:58.348
Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.

00:10:58.348 --> 00:11:06.048
For the foward is abomination to the Lord, but his secret is with the righteous.

00:11:07.808 --> 00:11:14.528
The curse of the Lord is in the house of the wicked, but he blesseth the habitation of the just.

00:11:15.768 --> 00:11:21.288
Surely he scorneth the scorners, but he giveth grace unto the lowly.

00:11:21.288 --> 00:11:28.808
The wise shall inherit glory, but shame shall be the promotion of fools.

00:11:47.631 --> 00:11:52.971
Hear ye children the instruction of a father, and attend to no understanding.

00:11:53.651 --> 00:11:57.451
For I give you good doctrine, forsake ye not my law.

00:11:57.871 --> 00:12:02.471
For I was my father's son, tender and only beloved in the sight of my mother.

00:12:02.691 --> 00:12:07.951
He taught me also, and said unto me, Let thine heart retain my words.

00:12:07.951 --> 00:12:10.231
Keep my commandments and live.

00:12:11.011 --> 00:12:17.351
Get wisdom, get understanding, forget it not, neither decline from the words of my mouth.

00:12:17.691 --> 00:12:23.591
Forsake her not, and she shall preserve thee, love her, and she shall keep thee.

00:12:24.071 --> 00:12:27.191
Wisdom is the principal thing, therefore get wisdom.

00:12:27.851 --> 00:12:30.431
And with all thy getting get understanding.

00:12:31.171 --> 00:12:33.671
Exalt her, and she shall promote thee.

00:12:33.671 --> 00:12:37.751
She shall bring thee to honor, when thou dost embrace her.

00:12:38.111 --> 00:12:44.491
She shall give to thine head an ornament of grace, a crown of glory shall she deliver to thee.

00:12:45.031 --> 00:12:52.191
Hear, O my son, and receive my sayings, and the years of thy life shall be many.

00:12:52.831 --> 00:12:57.591
I have taught thee in the way of wisdom, I have led thee in right paths.

00:12:57.591 --> 00:13:04.591
When thou goest, thy steps shall not be straightened, and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.

00:13:05.551 --> 00:13:12.071
Take fast hold of instruction, let her not go, keep her, for she is thy life.

00:13:13.331 --> 00:13:18.351
Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil men.

00:13:18.891 --> 00:13:23.411
Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.

00:13:23.411 --> 00:13:31.131
For they sleep not, except they have done mischief, and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause some to fall.

00:13:31.371 --> 00:13:35.451
For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.

00:13:35.831 --> 00:13:42.791
But the path of the just is as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.

00:13:43.671 --> 00:13:46.431
The way of the wicked is as darkness.

00:13:47.191 --> 00:13:49.691
They know not at what they stumble.

00:13:49.691 --> 00:13:56.071
My son, attend to my words, incline thine ear unto my sayings.

00:13:56.271 --> 00:14:01.591
Let them not depart from thine eyes, keep them in the midst of thine heart.

00:14:01.971 --> 00:14:07.531
For they are life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh.

00:14:08.211 --> 00:14:14.031
Keep thy heart with all diligence, for out of it are the issues of life.

00:14:14.411 --> 00:14:19.891
Put away from thee a foward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee.

00:14:20.191 --> 00:14:25.631
Let thine eyes look right on, and let thine eyelids look straight before thee.

00:14:26.031 --> 00:14:31.211
Ponder the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established.

00:14:31.811 --> 00:14:36.811
Turn not to the right hand, nor to the left, remove thy foot from evil.

00:14:55.656 --> 00:15:03.496
My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding, that thou mayest

00:15:03.496 --> 00:15:09.496
regard discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge, for the lips of a strange woman

00:15:09.496 --> 00:15:17.056
drop as in honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil, but her end is bitter as wormwood,

00:15:17.416 --> 00:15:26.336
sharp as a two-edged sword. Her feet go down to death, her steps take hold on hell, lest

00:15:26.336 --> 00:15:31.936
thou shouldest ponder the path of life her ways are movable, that thou canst not know

00:15:31.936 --> 00:15:39.396
them. Hear me now, therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth,

00:15:39.396 --> 00:15:45.796
remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house, lest thou give

00:15:45.796 --> 00:15:53.356
thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel, lest strangers be filled with thy

00:15:53.356 --> 00:16:00.636
wealth and thy labours be in the house of a stranger. And thou mourn at the last, when

00:16:00.636 --> 00:16:07.976
thy flesh and thy body are consumed, and say, How have I hated instruction? and my heart

00:16:08.496 --> 00:16:14.436
despised reproof, and have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear

00:16:14.436 --> 00:16:20.596
to them that instructed me. I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation

00:16:20.596 --> 00:16:28.336
and assembly. Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own

00:16:28.336 --> 00:16:35.256
well. Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of water in the streets, let them

00:16:35.256 --> 00:16:42.376
be only thine own, and not strangers with thee, let thy fountain be blessed, and rejoice

00:16:42.376 --> 00:16:49.796
with the wife of thy youth. Let her be as the loving hind and pleasant row, let her

00:16:49.796 --> 00:16:57.496
breasts satisfy thee at all times, and be thou ravished always with her love. And why

00:16:57.496 --> 00:17:03.796
wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?

00:17:04.256 --> 00:17:10.976
For the ways of man are before the eyes of the Lord, and he pondereth all his goings.

00:17:11.336 --> 00:17:18.536
His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his

00:17:18.536 --> 00:17:26.776
sins. He shall die without instruction, and in the greatness of his folly he shall go

00:17:26.776 --> 00:17:27.796
astray.

00:17:54.161 --> 00:18:00.141
thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.

00:18:01.181 --> 00:18:07.901
Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself. When thou art come into the hand of thy friend, go,

00:18:08.361 --> 00:18:16.661
humble thyself, and make sure thy friend. Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.

00:18:17.661 --> 00:18:24.641
Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.

00:18:25.021 --> 00:18:33.541
Go to the aunt thou sluggard, consider her ways, and be wise. Which, having no guide, overseer, or ruler,

00:18:34.061 --> 00:18:40.841
provideth her meat in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest. How long wilt thou sleep,

00:18:40.901 --> 00:18:48.601
O sluggard? When wilt thou arise out of thy sleep? Yet a little sleep, a little slumber,

00:18:48.601 --> 00:18:55.641
a little folding of the hands to sleep. So shall thy poverty come as one that travaileth,

00:18:56.181 --> 00:19:04.701
and thy want as an armed man. A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a foward mouth. He

00:19:04.701 --> 00:19:18.581
winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers. Fowardness is in his

00:19:18.581 --> 00:19:26.561
calamity come suddenly. Suddenly shall he be broken without remedy. These six things doth the

00:19:26.561 --> 00:19:36.381
Lord hate, yea, seven are an abomination unto him. A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed

00:19:36.381 --> 00:19:44.701
innocent blood, and heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to

00:19:44.701 --> 00:19:51.721
mischief, a false witness that speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.

00:19:52.421 --> 00:19:59.801
My son, keep thy father's commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother. Bind them

00:19:59.801 --> 00:20:06.141
continually upon thine heart, and tie them about thy neck. When thou goest it shall lead thee,

00:20:06.301 --> 00:20:13.041
when thou sleepest it shall keep thee, and when thou awakest it shall talk with thee. For the

00:20:13.041 --> 00:20:20.541
commandment is a lamp, and the law is light, and reproofs of instruction are the way of life. To

00:20:20.541 --> 00:20:28.181
keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman. Lest not after

00:20:28.181 --> 00:20:34.901
her beauty in thine heart, neither let her take thee with her eyelids. For by means of a horish

00:20:34.901 --> 00:20:41.181
woman a man is brought to a piece of bread, and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.

00:20:41.181 --> 00:20:50.861
Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned? Can one go upon hot coals, and his

00:20:50.861 --> 00:20:59.101
feet not be burned? So he that goeth into his neighbor's wife, whosoever toucheth her, shall

00:20:59.101 --> 00:21:06.001
not be innocent. Men do not despise a thief if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry.

00:21:06.001 --> 00:21:13.821
But if he be found, he shall restore sevenfold, he shall give all the substance of his house.

00:21:14.621 --> 00:21:20.341
But whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding, he that doeth it destroyeth his

00:21:20.341 --> 00:21:29.781
own soul. A wound and dishonor shall he get, and his reproach shall not be wiped away. For jealousy

00:21:29.781 --> 00:21:38.061
is the rage of a man, therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance. He will not regard any

00:21:38.061 --> 00:21:43.701
ransom, neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts.

00:22:02.503 --> 00:22:08.023
My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.

00:22:08.263 --> 00:22:13.043
Keep my commandments and live, and my law as the apple of thine eye.

00:22:14.343 --> 00:22:18.623
Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.

00:22:18.623 --> 00:22:24.343
Say unto wisdom, thou art my sister, and call understanding thy kinswoman,

00:22:25.003 --> 00:22:28.063
that they may keep thee from the strange woman,

00:22:28.403 --> 00:22:31.563
from the stranger which flattereth with her words.

00:22:32.103 --> 00:22:36.103
For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,

00:22:36.583 --> 00:22:41.563
and beheld among the simple ones I discerned among the youths

00:22:41.563 --> 00:22:43.943
a young man void of understanding.

00:22:43.943 --> 00:22:48.083
Passing through the street near her corner, he went the way to her house.

00:22:49.543 --> 00:22:53.783
In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night.

00:22:54.303 --> 00:22:58.103
And behold, there met him a woman, with the attire of an harlot,

00:22:58.603 --> 00:22:59.863
and subtle of heart.

00:23:00.463 --> 00:23:04.323
She is loud and stubborn, her feet abide not in her house.

00:23:04.703 --> 00:23:09.423
Now is she without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.

00:23:09.423 --> 00:23:14.803
So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him,

00:23:15.123 --> 00:23:19.923
I have peace offerings with me, this day have I paid my vows.

00:23:20.543 --> 00:23:25.023
Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face,

00:23:25.223 --> 00:23:26.663
and I have found thee.

00:23:27.003 --> 00:23:30.283
I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry,

00:23:30.663 --> 00:23:33.883
with carved works, with fine linen of Egypt.

00:23:34.203 --> 00:23:38.243
I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.

00:23:38.243 --> 00:23:42.643
Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning.

00:23:43.043 --> 00:23:45.743
Let us solace ourselves with loves.

00:23:46.663 --> 00:23:50.643
For the good man is not at home, he has gone a long journey.

00:23:51.023 --> 00:23:53.223
He hath taken a bag of money with him,

00:23:53.563 --> 00:23:56.303
and will come home at the day appointed.

00:23:56.623 --> 00:24:00.523
With her much fair speech, she caused him to yield.

00:24:01.223 --> 00:24:03.943
With the flattering of her lips she forced him,

00:24:04.303 --> 00:24:06.363
he goeth after her straightway.

00:24:06.783 --> 00:24:09.123
As an ox goeth to the slaughter,

00:24:09.763 --> 00:24:12.983
or as a fool to the correction of the stocks,

00:24:13.583 --> 00:24:15.643
till a dart strike through his liver,

00:24:16.083 --> 00:24:18.543
as a bird hasteth to the snare,

00:24:19.243 --> 00:24:21.943
and knoweth not that it is for his life.

00:24:22.843 --> 00:24:25.763
Harken unto me now therefore, oh ye children,

00:24:26.403 --> 00:24:28.783
and attend to the words of my mouth.

00:24:29.163 --> 00:24:31.403
Let not thine heart decline to her ways,

00:24:31.843 --> 00:24:33.743
go not astray in her paths,

00:24:33.743 --> 00:24:36.703
for she hath cast down many wounded,

00:24:37.123 --> 00:24:41.143
yea, many strong men have been slain by her.

00:24:41.723 --> 00:24:44.263
Her house is the way to hell,

00:24:44.643 --> 00:24:48.663
going down to the chambers of death.

00:25:07.784 --> 00:25:11.524
Doth not wisdom cry, And understanding put forth her voice?

00:25:12.524 --> 00:25:18.144
She standeth in the top of high places, By the way, in the places of the paths.

00:25:18.484 --> 00:25:21.804
She crieth at the gates, At the entry of the city,

00:25:22.024 --> 00:25:24.024
At the coming in at the doors.

00:25:25.344 --> 00:25:27.004
Unto you, O men, I call.

00:25:27.004 --> 00:25:30.604
And my voice is to the sons of man.

00:25:31.424 --> 00:25:37.744
O ye simple understand wisdom, And ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.

00:25:38.304 --> 00:25:44.704
Hear, for I will speak of excellent things, And the opening of my lips shall be right

00:25:44.704 --> 00:25:45.384
things.

00:25:46.104 --> 00:25:50.824
For my mouth shall speak truth, And wickedness is an abomination to my lips.

00:25:51.784 --> 00:25:54.024
All the words of my mouth are in righteousness.

00:25:54.024 --> 00:25:57.264
There is nothing foward or perverse in them.

00:25:57.984 --> 00:26:03.084
They are all plain to him that understandeth, And right to them that find knowledge.

00:26:03.864 --> 00:26:09.484
Receive my instruction, and not silver, And knowledge rather than choice gold.

00:26:09.804 --> 00:26:14.984
For wisdom is better than rubies, And all the things that may be desired,

00:26:15.784 --> 00:26:17.884
Are not to be compared to it.

00:26:17.884 --> 00:26:24.144
I wisdom dwell with prudence, And find out knowledge of witty inventions.

00:26:25.644 --> 00:26:31.684
The fear of the Lord is to hate evil, Pride and arrogance in the evil way,

00:26:31.904 --> 00:26:33.924
And the foward mouth do I hate.

00:26:34.904 --> 00:26:37.104
Council is mine and sound wisdom.

00:26:38.024 --> 00:26:40.544
I am understanding, I have strength.

00:26:41.084 --> 00:26:44.864
By me kings reign, And princes decree justice.

00:26:45.224 --> 00:26:50.684
By me princes rule, And nobles even all the judges of the earth.

00:26:51.304 --> 00:26:56.884
I love them that love me, And those that seek me early shall find me.

00:26:57.564 --> 00:27:02.804
Riches and honor are with me, Yea, durable riches and righteousness.

00:27:03.824 --> 00:27:07.404
My fruit is better than gold, Yea, than fine gold,

00:27:07.624 --> 00:27:09.764
And my revenue than choice silver.

00:27:10.724 --> 00:27:16.044
I lead in the way of righteousness, In the midst of the paths of judgment,

00:27:16.424 --> 00:27:19.664
That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance,

00:27:20.184 --> 00:27:21.744
And I will fill their treasures.

00:27:22.604 --> 00:27:25.204
The Lord possessed me in the beginning of His way,

00:27:25.324 --> 00:27:27.024
Before His works of old.

00:27:27.584 --> 00:27:31.464
I was set up from everlasting, From the beginning or ever the earth was.

00:27:32.404 --> 00:27:35.604
When there were no depths, I was brought forth,

00:27:35.904 --> 00:27:38.864
When there were no fountains abounding with water.

00:27:38.864 --> 00:27:44.064
Before the mountains were settled, Before the hills was I brought forth.

00:27:44.964 --> 00:27:48.904
While as yet He had not made the earth, Nor the fields, nor the highest part

00:27:48.904 --> 00:27:52.884
Of the dust of the world, When He prepared the heavens, I was there,

00:27:53.104 --> 00:27:56.284
When He set a compass upon the face of the depth,

00:27:56.784 --> 00:28:01.464
When He established the clouds above, When He strengthened the fountains of the deep,

00:28:02.364 --> 00:28:07.504
When He gave the sea His decree, That the water should not pass His commandment,

00:28:07.504 --> 00:28:10.404
When He appointed the foundations of the earth.

00:28:11.184 --> 00:28:14.524
Then I was by Him, as one brought up with Him,

00:28:14.844 --> 00:28:18.864
And I was daily His delight, rejoicing always before Him,

00:28:19.144 --> 00:28:22.424
Rejoicing in the habitable part of His earth.

00:28:23.024 --> 00:28:25.424
And my delights were with the sons of men.

00:28:25.884 --> 00:28:29.664
Now therefore hearken unto me, O ye children,

00:28:30.364 --> 00:28:32.944
For blessed are they that keep my ways,

00:28:33.444 --> 00:28:36.524
Hear instruction and be wise and refuse it not.

00:28:36.524 --> 00:28:40.004
Blessed is the man that heareth me,

00:28:41.124 --> 00:28:44.764
Watching daily at my gates, waiting at the post of my doors.

00:28:45.624 --> 00:28:51.184
For whoso findeth me, findeth life, And shall obtain favour of the Lord.

00:28:51.524 --> 00:28:54.644
But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul.

00:28:55.584 --> 00:28:57.444
All they that hate me love death.

00:29:17.831 --> 00:29:19.571
Wisdom hath builded her house.

00:29:20.071 --> 00:29:22.551
She hath hewn out her seven pillars.

00:29:23.011 --> 00:29:24.511
She hath killed her beasts.

00:29:24.771 --> 00:29:26.351
She hath mingled her wine.

00:29:26.651 --> 00:29:28.431
She hath also furnished her table.

00:29:28.791 --> 00:29:30.571
She hath set forth her maidens.

00:29:31.151 --> 00:29:34.251
She crieth upon the highest places of the city.

00:29:35.011 --> 00:29:37.951
Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither.

00:29:38.291 --> 00:29:41.591
As for him that wanteth understanding, she sayeth to him,

00:29:41.791 --> 00:29:46.191
Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine which I have mingled.

00:29:46.611 --> 00:29:50.491
Forsake the foolish and live, and go in the way of understanding.

00:29:51.491 --> 00:29:54.591
He that reproveth a scorner, geteth to himself shame.

00:29:55.231 --> 00:29:58.651
And he that rebuketh a wicked man, geteth himself a blot.

00:29:59.631 --> 00:30:02.931
Reprove not a scorner, lest he hate thee.

00:30:03.451 --> 00:30:07.511
Rebuke a wise man, and he will love thee.

00:30:08.831 --> 00:30:13.071
Give instruction to a wise man, and he will be yet wiser.

00:30:13.751 --> 00:30:17.071
Teach a just man, and he will increase in learning.

00:30:18.251 --> 00:30:21.331
The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom,

00:30:21.691 --> 00:30:24.151
and the knowledge of the holy is understanding.

00:30:24.871 --> 00:30:27.231
For by me thy ways shall be multiplied,

00:30:27.771 --> 00:30:30.251
and the years of thy life shall be increased.

00:30:30.771 --> 00:30:34.011
If thou be wise, thou shalt be wise for thyself.

00:30:34.391 --> 00:30:37.691
But if thou scornest, thou alone shalt bear it.

00:30:38.631 --> 00:30:40.611
A foolish woman is calamitous.

00:30:41.271 --> 00:30:43.631
She is simple, and knoweth nothing.

00:30:44.271 --> 00:30:46.391
For she sitteth at the door of her house,

00:30:46.991 --> 00:30:49.351
on a seat in the high places of the city,

00:30:49.711 --> 00:30:52.931
to call passengers who go right on their ways.

00:30:53.591 --> 00:30:55.991
Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither.

00:30:56.431 --> 00:30:59.711
As for him that wanteth understanding, she sayeth to him,

00:31:00.231 --> 00:31:05.531
Stolen waters are sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.

00:31:06.331 --> 00:31:08.711
But he knoweth not that the dead are in there,

00:31:08.731 --> 00:31:11.371
and that her guests are in the depths of hell.

00:31:30.269 --> 00:31:36.929
THE PROVERBS OF SOLOMON A wise son maketh a glad father.

00:31:37.529 --> 00:31:40.869
But a foolish son is the heaviness of his mother.

00:31:41.949 --> 00:31:47.109
Treasures of wickedness profit nothing, But righteousness delivereth from death.

00:31:47.689 --> 00:31:51.449
The Lord will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish,

00:31:51.709 --> 00:31:54.629
But he casteth away the substance of the wicked.

00:31:55.829 --> 00:31:59.269
He becomeeth poor that dealeth with a slack hand,

00:32:00.009 --> 00:32:02.469
But the hand of the diligent maketh rich.

00:32:03.789 --> 00:32:06.549
He that gathereth in summer is a wise son,

00:32:07.309 --> 00:32:11.409
But he that sleepeth in harvest is a son that causeth shame.

00:32:12.329 --> 00:32:17.909
Blessings are upon the head of the just, But violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.

00:32:19.349 --> 00:32:25.809
The memory of the just is blessed, But the name of the wicked shall rot.

00:32:26.749 --> 00:32:32.729
The wise in heart will receive commandments, But a prating fool shall fall.

00:32:33.709 --> 00:32:40.969
He that walketh uprightly walketh surely, But he that perverteth his ways shall be known.

00:32:41.409 --> 00:32:48.009
He that winketh with the eye causeth sorrow, But a prating fool shall fall.

00:32:48.829 --> 00:32:55.869
The mouth of a righteous man is a well of life, But violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.

00:32:56.909 --> 00:33:03.109
Hatred stirreth up strifes, But love covereth all sins.

00:33:04.029 --> 00:33:07.609
In the lips of him that hath understanding wisdom is found,

00:33:08.329 --> 00:33:12.329
But a rod is for the back of him that is void of understanding.

00:33:13.709 --> 00:33:19.049
Wise men lay up knowledge, But the mouth of the foolish is near destruction.

00:33:19.669 --> 00:33:26.449
The rich man's wealth is his strong city, The destruction of the poor is their poverty.

00:33:27.049 --> 00:33:32.269
The labor of the righteous tendeth to life, The fruit of the wicked to sin.

00:33:32.809 --> 00:33:38.929
He is in the way of life that keepeth instruction, But he that refuseth reproof ereth.

00:33:40.049 --> 00:33:45.849
He that hideeth hatred with lying lips, And he that uttereth a slander is a fool.

00:33:46.989 --> 00:33:53.929
In the multitude of words there wanteth not sin, But he that refraineth his lips is wise.

00:33:54.669 --> 00:34:01.509
The tongue of the just is as choice silver, The heart of the wicked is little worth.

00:34:02.269 --> 00:34:07.609
The lips of the righteous feed many, But fools die for want of wisdom.

00:34:09.329 --> 00:34:14.589
The blessing of the Lord it maketh rich, And he addeth no sorrow with it.

00:34:15.489 --> 00:34:21.409
It is as sport to a fool to do mischief, But a man of understanding hath wisdom.

00:34:22.849 --> 00:34:28.589
The fear of the wicked it shall come upon him, But the desire of the righteous shall be granted.

00:34:29.309 --> 00:34:37.549
As the whirlwind passeth, so is the wicked no more, But the righteous is an everlasting foundation.

00:34:38.629 --> 00:34:46.289
As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, So is the sluggard to them that send him.

00:34:48.289 --> 00:34:54.269
The fear of the Lord prolongeth days, But the years of the wicked shall be shortened.

00:34:55.889 --> 00:35:02.269
The hope of the righteous shall be gladness, But the expectation of the wicked shall perish.

00:35:04.229 --> 00:35:10.749
The way of the Lord is strength to the upright, But destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.

00:35:11.829 --> 00:35:16.829
The righteous shall never be removed, But the wicked shall not inhabit the earth.

00:35:17.889 --> 00:35:24.249
The mouth of the just bringeth forth wisdom, But the foward tongue shall be cut out.

00:35:25.809 --> 00:35:32.709
The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable, But the mouth of the wicked speaketh fowardness.

00:35:51.796 --> 00:35:58.896
A false balance is abomination to the Lord, But a just wait is his delight.

00:36:00.016 --> 00:36:05.456
When pride cometh, then cometh shame, But with the lowly is wisdom.

00:36:05.456 --> 00:36:12.616
The integrity of the upright shall guide them, But the perverseness of transgressors shall

00:36:12.616 --> 00:36:20.116
destroy them. Riches profit not in the day of wrath, But righteousness delivereth from death.

00:36:21.596 --> 00:36:27.676
The righteousness of the perfect shall direct his way, But the wicked shall fall by his own

00:36:27.676 --> 00:36:35.436
wickedness. The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them, But transgressors shall be taken

00:36:35.436 --> 00:36:43.836
in their own naughtiness. When a wicked man dieth, his expectation shall perish, and the hope of

00:36:43.836 --> 00:36:49.796
unjust men perisheth. The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked cometh in his

00:36:49.796 --> 00:36:56.896
stead. An hypocrite with his mouth destroyeth his neighbor, but through knowledge shall the just be

00:36:56.896 --> 00:37:03.916
delivered. When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth, and when the wicked perish,

00:37:03.916 --> 00:37:11.776
there is shouting. By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted, but it is overthrown by the

00:37:11.776 --> 00:37:18.396
mouth of the wicked. He that is void of wisdom despiseth his neighbor, but a man of understanding

00:37:18.396 --> 00:37:26.756
holdeth his peace. A tale-bearer reveals secrets, but he that is of a faithful spirit concealeth

00:37:26.756 --> 00:37:33.676
the matter. Where no counsel is, the people fall, but in the multitude of counselors there is safety.

00:37:33.676 --> 00:37:42.876
He that is surety for a stranger shall smart for it, and he that hateth suretorship is sure. A gracious

00:37:42.876 --> 00:37:50.616
woman retaineth honor, and strong men retain riches. The merciful man doeth good to his own soul,

00:37:51.156 --> 00:37:58.996
but he that is cruel trebleth his own flesh. The wicked worketh a deceitful work, but to him that

00:37:58.996 --> 00:38:08.676
righteousness shall be a sure reward. As righteousness tendeth to life, so he that pursueth evil pursueth

00:38:08.676 --> 00:38:16.796
it to his own death. They that are of a foward heart are abomination to the Lord, but such as

00:38:16.796 --> 00:38:23.976
are upright in their way are his delight. Though hand joined in hand, the wicked shall not be

00:38:23.976 --> 00:38:32.676
punished, but the seed of the righteous shall be delivered. As a jewel of gold in a swine snout,

00:38:33.436 --> 00:38:40.036
so is a fair woman which is without discretion. The desire of the righteous is only good,

00:38:40.636 --> 00:38:46.936
but the expectation of the wicked is wrath. There is that scattereth, and yet increaseth,

00:38:46.936 --> 00:38:55.036
and there is that withholdeth more than his meat, but it tendeth to poverty. The liberal soul shall

00:38:55.036 --> 00:39:03.336
be made fat, and he that watereth shall be watered also himself. He that withholdeth corn,

00:39:03.736 --> 00:39:11.166
the people shall curse him, but blessing shall be upon the head of him that selleth it. He that

00:39:11.166 --> 00:39:19.906
seeketh good procureth favor, but he that seeketh mischief it shall come unto him. He that trusteth

00:39:19.906 --> 00:39:26.746
in his riches shall fall, but the righteous shall flourish as a branch. He that trebleth his own

00:39:26.746 --> 00:39:38.606
house shall inherit the wind, and the fool shall be servant to the wise of heart. The fruit of the

00:39:38.606 --> 00:39:46.146
is wise. Behold, the righteous shall be recompensed in the earth, much more the wicked in the sinner.

00:40:04.984 --> 00:40:07.524
Whoso loveth instruction loveth knowledge,

00:40:08.344 --> 00:40:11.184
but he that hateth reproof is brutish.

00:40:12.104 --> 00:40:14.564
A good man obtaineth favor of the Lord,

00:40:15.284 --> 00:40:18.104
but a man of wicked devices will he condemn.

00:40:19.804 --> 00:40:22.604
A man shall not be established by wickedness,

00:40:22.604 --> 00:40:26.104
but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.

00:40:27.264 --> 00:40:35.024
A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband, but she that maketh ashamed is as rottenness in his bones.

00:40:36.464 --> 00:40:41.384
The thoughts of the righteous are right, but the counsels of the wicked are deceit.

00:40:42.044 --> 00:40:48.064
The words of the wicked are to lie and wait for blood, but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them.

00:40:48.064 --> 00:40:53.304
The wicked are overthrown and are not, but the house of the righteous shall stand.

00:40:54.864 --> 00:41:01.124
A man shall be commended according to his wisdom, but he that is of a perverse heart shall be despised.

00:41:02.664 --> 00:41:09.604
He that is despised and hath a servant is better than he that honoreth himself and lacketh bread.

00:41:10.824 --> 00:41:16.904
A righteous man regardeth the life of the beast, but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.

00:41:18.884 --> 00:41:22.664
He that tilleth his land shall be satisfied with bread,

00:41:23.404 --> 00:41:26.944
but he that followeth vain persons is void of understanding.

00:41:28.224 --> 00:41:30.724
The wicked desireth the net of evil men,

00:41:31.464 --> 00:41:33.724
but the root of the righteous yieldeth fruit.

00:41:35.524 --> 00:41:38.704
The wicked is snared by the transgression of his lips,

00:41:39.344 --> 00:41:41.404
but the just shall come out of trouble.

00:41:41.404 --> 00:41:45.544
A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth,

00:41:46.044 --> 00:41:50.244
and the recompense of a man's hands shall be rendered unto him.

00:41:51.324 --> 00:41:53.824
The way of a fool is right in his own eyes,

00:41:54.404 --> 00:41:57.304
but he that hearkeneth unto counsel is wise.

00:41:57.944 --> 00:42:03.044
A fool's wrath is presently known, but a prudent man covereth shame.

00:42:04.524 --> 00:42:07.244
He that speaketh truth showeth forth righteousness,

00:42:08.184 --> 00:42:10.284
but a false witness deceit.

00:42:10.284 --> 00:42:13.964
There is that speaketh like the piercings of a sword,

00:42:15.024 --> 00:42:16.824
but the tongue of the wise is health.

00:42:18.264 --> 00:42:21.024
The lip of truth shall be established for ever,

00:42:21.624 --> 00:42:24.084
but a lying tongue is but for a moment.

00:42:25.424 --> 00:42:27.844
Deceit is in the heart of them that imagine evil,

00:42:28.444 --> 00:42:30.844
but to the counselors of peace is joy.

00:42:32.024 --> 00:42:34.424
There shall no evil happen to the just,

00:42:35.024 --> 00:42:37.484
but the wicked shall be filled with mischief.

00:42:38.164 --> 00:42:41.144
Lying lips are abomination to the Lord,

00:42:41.584 --> 00:42:44.164
but they that deal truly are his delight.

00:42:45.804 --> 00:42:47.964
A prudent man concealeth knowledge,

00:42:48.924 --> 00:42:51.584
but the heart of fools proclaimeth foolishness.

00:42:52.084 --> 00:42:54.524
The hand of the diligent shall bear rule,

00:42:55.244 --> 00:42:58.104
but the slothful shall be under tribute.

00:42:59.464 --> 00:43:02.244
Heaviness in the heart of man maketh it stoop,

00:43:03.364 --> 00:43:05.264
but a good word maketh it glad.

00:43:06.544 --> 00:43:09.684
The righteous is more excellent than his neighbor,

00:43:10.044 --> 00:43:12.424
but the way of the wicked seduceth them.

00:43:12.844 --> 00:43:16.484
The slothful man roasteth not that which he took in hunting,

00:43:17.124 --> 00:43:19.744
but the substance of a diligent man is precious.

00:43:20.124 --> 00:43:22.304
In the way of righteousness is life,

00:43:22.584 --> 00:43:25.344
and in the pathway thereof there is no death.

00:43:44.242 --> 00:43:51.482
A wise son heareth his father's instruction, But a scornor heareth not rebuke.

00:43:52.662 --> 00:43:58.622
A man shall eat good by the fruit of his mouth, But the soul of the transgressor shall eat

00:43:58.622 --> 00:43:59.522
violence.

00:44:00.542 --> 00:44:08.182
He that keepeth his mouth keepeth his life, But he that openeth wide his lips shall have

00:44:08.182 --> 00:44:08.922
destruction.

00:44:10.622 --> 00:44:16.942
The soul of a sluggard desireth and hath nothing, But the soul of the diligent shall

00:44:16.942 --> 00:44:17.882
be made fat.

00:44:19.602 --> 00:44:26.122
A righteous man hateth lying, But a wicked man is loathsome and cometh to shame.

00:44:27.742 --> 00:44:33.322
Righteousness keepeth him that is upright in the way, But wickedness overthroweth the

00:44:33.322 --> 00:44:33.762
sinner.

00:44:34.742 --> 00:44:37.822
There is that maketh himself rich, yet hath nothing.

00:44:38.682 --> 00:44:42.462
There is that maketh himself poor, yet hath great riches.

00:44:43.902 --> 00:44:49.542
The ransom of a man's life are his riches, But the poor heareth not rebuke.

00:44:50.542 --> 00:44:56.502
The light of the righteous rejoiceth, But the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.

00:44:58.022 --> 00:45:04.102
Only in pride cometh contention, But with the well advised is wisdom.

00:45:05.842 --> 00:45:13.282
Wealth gotten by vanity shall be diminished, But he that gathereth by labour shall increase.

00:45:14.542 --> 00:45:21.682
Hope deferred maketh the heart sick, But when the desire cometh it is a tree of life.

00:45:22.442 --> 00:45:28.082
Whoso despiseth the word shall be destroyed, But he that feareth the commandment shall

00:45:28.082 --> 00:45:28.822
be rewarded.

00:45:30.202 --> 00:45:35.522
The law of the wise is a fountain of life, To depart from the snares of death.

00:45:36.602 --> 00:45:42.162
Good understanding giveth favour, But the way of transgressors is hard.

00:45:44.722 --> 00:45:50.102
Every prudent man dealeth with knowledge, But a fool layeth open his folly.

00:45:51.402 --> 00:45:56.922
A wicked messenger falleth into mischief, But a faithful ambassador is health.

00:45:58.842 --> 00:46:05.182
Poverty and shame shall be to him that refuseth instruction, But he that regardeth reproof

00:46:05.182 --> 00:46:06.522
shall be honoured.

00:46:07.342 --> 00:46:14.482
The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul, But it is abomination to fools to depart

00:46:14.482 --> 00:46:15.222
from evil.

00:46:17.742 --> 00:46:23.642
He that walketh with wise men shall be wise, But a companion of fools shall be destroyed.

00:46:25.162 --> 00:46:30.222
Evil pursueth sinners, But to the righteous good shall be repaid.

00:46:31.522 --> 00:46:38.322
A good man liveth an inheritance to his children's children, And the wealth of a sinner is laid

00:46:38.322 --> 00:46:39.542
up for the just.

00:46:41.022 --> 00:46:46.562
Much food is in the tillage of the poor, But there is that is destroyed for want of judgment.

00:46:47.862 --> 00:46:54.002
He that spareth the rod hateth his son, But he that loveth him chasteneth him betimes.

00:46:54.742 --> 00:47:00.202
The righteous eateth to the satisfying of his soul, But the belly of the wicked shall

00:47:00.202 --> 00:47:00.682
want.

00:47:20.064 --> 00:47:26.964
Every wise woman buildeth her house, But the foolish plucketh it down with her hands.

00:47:27.784 --> 00:47:30.824
He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the Lord,

00:47:31.544 --> 00:47:34.904
But he that is perverse in his ways despiseth him.

00:47:35.404 --> 00:47:42.004
In the mouth of the foolish is a rod of pride, But the lips of the wise shall preserve them.

00:47:42.784 --> 00:47:48.964
Where no oxen are the crib is clean, But much increases by the strength of the ox.

00:47:50.164 --> 00:47:55.284
A faithful witness will not lie, But a false witness will utter lies.

00:47:56.264 --> 00:48:02.744
A scornor seeketh wisdom and findeth it not, But knowledge is easy unto him that understandeth.

00:48:03.464 --> 00:48:09.564
Go from the presence of a foolish man, When thou perceivest not in him the lips of knowledge.

00:48:10.764 --> 00:48:17.324
The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way, But the folly of fools is deceit.

00:48:18.144 --> 00:48:22.924
Fools make a mock at sin, But among the righteous there is favour.

00:48:23.964 --> 00:48:30.024
The heart knoweth his own bitterness, And a stranger doth not intermeddle with his joy.

00:48:30.704 --> 00:48:37.144
The house of the wicked shall be overthrown, But the tabernacle of the upright shall flourish.

00:48:38.064 --> 00:48:45.704
There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, But the end thereof are the ways of death.

00:48:47.184 --> 00:48:52.884
Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful, And the end of that mirth is heaviness.

00:48:53.884 --> 00:48:58.164
The backslider in heart shall be filled with his own ways,

00:48:59.364 --> 00:49:02.724
And a good man shall be satisfied from himself.

00:49:04.024 --> 00:49:09.304
The simple believeth every word, But the prudent man looketh well to his going.

00:49:10.724 --> 00:49:16.924
A wise man feareth and departeth from evil, But the fool rageth and is confident.

00:49:17.824 --> 00:49:24.504
He that is soon angry dealeth foolishly, And a man of wicked devices is hated.

00:49:25.784 --> 00:49:30.644
The simple inherit folly, But the prudent are crowned with knowledge.

00:49:32.024 --> 00:49:37.784
The evil bow before the good, And the wicked at the gates of the righteous.

00:49:38.784 --> 00:49:43.264
The poor is hated even of his own neighbour, But the rich hath many friends.

00:49:44.604 --> 00:49:51.404
He that despiseth his neighbour sinneth, But he that hath mercy on the poor happy is he.

00:49:52.444 --> 00:49:58.404
Do they not err that devise evil? But mercy and truth shall be to them that devise good.

00:49:59.704 --> 00:50:05.404
In all labour there is profit, But the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.

00:50:07.064 --> 00:50:13.244
The crown of the wise is their riches, But the foolishness of fools is folly.

00:50:14.504 --> 00:50:20.444
A true witness delivereth souls, But a deceitful witness speaketh lies.

00:50:21.624 --> 00:50:27.424
In the fear of the Lord is strong confidence, And his children shall have a place of refuge.

00:50:28.524 --> 00:50:33.604
The fear of the Lord is a fountain of life, To depart from the snares of death.

00:50:34.644 --> 00:50:41.104
In the multitude of people is the King's honour, But in the want of people is the destruction of

00:50:41.104 --> 00:50:49.164
the prince. He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding, But he that is hasty of spirit

00:50:49.164 --> 00:50:57.924
exalteth folly. A sound heart is the life of the flesh, But envy the rottenness of the bones.

00:50:59.024 --> 00:51:06.424
He that oppresseth the poor reproacheth his maker, But he that honoureth him hath mercy on the poor.

00:51:07.424 --> 00:51:13.824
The wicked are driven away in their wickedness, But the righteous hath hope in his death.

00:51:14.944 --> 00:51:20.764
Wisdom resteth in the heart of him that hath understanding, But that which is in the midst

00:51:20.764 --> 00:51:29.444
of fools is made known. Righteousness exalteth a nation, But sin is a reproach to any people.

00:51:30.744 --> 00:51:36.404
The King's favour is toward a wise servant, But his wrath is against him that causes him to die.

00:51:58.105 --> 00:52:03.085
A soft answer turneth away wrath, But grievous words stir up anger.

00:52:03.825 --> 00:52:09.885
The tongue of the wise useth knowledge aright, But the mouth of fools poureth out foolishness.

00:52:10.405 --> 00:52:14.485
The eyes of the Lord are in every place, Beholding the evil and the good.

00:52:14.485 --> 00:52:21.465
A wholesome tongue is a tree of life, But perverseness therein is a breach in the spirit.

00:52:22.165 --> 00:52:27.905
A fool despiseth his father's instruction, But he that regardeth reproof is prudent.

00:52:28.385 --> 00:52:33.605
In the house of the righteous is much treasure, But in the revenues of the wicked is trouble.

00:52:34.465 --> 00:52:39.305
The lips of the wise disperse knowledge, But the heart of the foolish doeth not so.

00:52:39.305 --> 00:52:45.985
The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the Lord, But the prayer of the upright is his delight.

00:52:47.645 --> 00:52:54.465
The way of the wicked is an abomination unto the Lord, But he loveth him that followeth after righteousness.

00:52:55.325 --> 00:53:01.205
Correction is grievous unto him that forsaketh the way, And he that hateth reproof shall die.

00:53:01.845 --> 00:53:06.945
Hell and destruction are before the Lord, How much more than the hearts of the children of men.

00:53:06.945 --> 00:53:13.025
A scornor loveth not one that reprooveth him, Neither will he go unto the wise.

00:53:13.925 --> 00:53:20.265
A merry heart maketh a cheerful countenance, But by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.

00:53:21.005 --> 00:53:27.985
The heart of him that hath understanding seeketh knowledge, But the mouth of fools feedeth on foolishness.

00:53:28.305 --> 00:53:34.205
All the days of the afflicted are evil, But he that is of a merry heart hath a continual feast.

00:53:34.205 --> 00:53:40.545
Better is little with the fear of the Lord Than great treasure and trouble therewith.

00:53:41.245 --> 00:53:47.545
Better is a dinner of herbs where love is Than a stalled ox and hatred therewith.

00:53:48.965 --> 00:53:56.465
A wrathful man stirth up strife, But he that is slow to anger appeaseth strife.

00:53:56.945 --> 00:54:03.745
The way of the slothful man is as an hedge of thorns, But the way of the righteous is made plain.

00:54:04.905 --> 00:54:11.065
A wise son maketh a glad father, But a foolish man despiseth his mother.

00:54:12.065 --> 00:54:19.045
Folly is joy to him that is destitute of wisdom, But a man of understanding walketh uprightly.

00:54:20.145 --> 00:54:26.505
Without counsel purposes are disappointed, But in the multitude of counsellors they are established.

00:54:27.545 --> 00:54:36.685
A man hath joy by the answer of his mouth, And a word spoken in due season. How good is it!

00:54:37.705 --> 00:54:42.505
The way of life is above to the wise, That he may depart from hell beneath.

00:54:43.545 --> 00:54:48.805
The Lord will destroy the house of the proud, But he will establish the border of the widow.

00:54:48.805 --> 00:54:56.745
The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the Lord, But the words of the pure are pleasant words.

00:54:57.525 --> 00:55:04.685
He that is greedy of gain troubleth his own house, But he that hateth gifts shall live.

00:55:06.325 --> 00:55:12.365
The heart of the righteous studieth to answer, But the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.

00:55:12.365 --> 00:55:18.625
The Lord is far from the wicked, But he heareth the prayer of the righteous.

00:55:19.825 --> 00:55:25.845
The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart, And a good report maketh the bones fat.

00:55:27.265 --> 00:55:31.125
The ear that heareth the reproof of life abideth among the wise.

00:55:32.645 --> 00:55:39.325
He that refuseth instruction despiseth his own soul, But he that heareth reproof geteth understanding.

00:55:39.325 --> 00:55:46.825
The fear of the Lord is the instruction of wisdom, And before honor is humility.

00:56:05.755 --> 00:56:11.535
The preparations of the heart in man, and the answer of the tongue, is from the Lord.

00:56:12.035 --> 00:56:17.635
All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes, but the Lord weigheth the spirits.

00:56:18.735 --> 00:56:23.595
Commit thy works unto the Lord, and thy thoughts shall be established.

00:56:24.355 --> 00:56:30.115
The Lord hath made all things for himself, yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.

00:56:31.155 --> 00:56:34.815
Every one that is proud in heart is an abomination to the Lord.

00:56:35.815 --> 00:56:39.575
Though hand joined in hand, he shall not be unpunished.

00:56:40.715 --> 00:56:46.695
By mercy and truth iniquity is purged, and by the fear of the Lord men depart from evil.

00:56:47.615 --> 00:56:53.155
When a man's ways please the Lord, he maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.

00:56:53.155 --> 00:56:58.515
Better is a little with righteousness, than great revenues without right.

00:56:59.875 --> 00:57:04.795
A man's heart deviseth his way, but the Lord directeth his steps.

00:57:05.715 --> 00:57:11.435
A divine sentence is in the lips of the King, his mouth transgresseth not in judgment.

00:57:12.315 --> 00:57:18.495
A just weight and balance are the Lord's, all the weights of the bag are his work.

00:57:18.495 --> 00:57:25.435
It is an abomination to kings to commit wickedness, for the throne is established by righteousness.

00:57:26.955 --> 00:57:32.155
Righteous lips are the delight of kings, and they love him that speaketh right.

00:57:33.375 --> 00:57:39.115
The wrath of a king is as messengers of death, but a wise man will pacify it.

00:57:39.715 --> 00:57:46.595
In the light of the king's countenance is life, and his favor is as a cloud of the latter rain.

00:57:46.595 --> 00:57:54.335
How much better is it to get wisdom than gold, and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver?

00:57:55.055 --> 00:57:57.995
The highway of the upright is to depart from evil.

00:57:58.615 --> 00:58:01.875
He that keepeth his way, preserveth his soul.

00:58:02.835 --> 00:58:08.395
Pride goeth before destruction, and in haughty spirit before a fall.

00:58:09.195 --> 00:58:16.175
Better it is to be of a humble spirit with the lowly, than to divide the spoil with the proud.

00:58:17.255 --> 00:58:24.355
He that handleeth a matter wisely shall find good, and whoso trusteth in the Lord happy is he.

00:58:25.535 --> 00:58:31.515
The wise in heart shall be called prudent, and the sweetness of the lips increaseeth learning.

00:58:33.055 --> 00:58:39.275
Understanding is a wellspring of life unto him that hath it, but the instruction of fools is folly.

00:58:40.415 --> 00:58:45.415
The heart of the wise teacheth his mouth, and addeth learning to his lips.

00:58:46.595 --> 00:58:51.915
Pleasant words are as an honeycomb sweet to the soul and health to the bones.

00:58:53.035 --> 00:58:59.115
There is a way that seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.

00:59:00.455 --> 00:59:05.935
He that laboreth, laboreth for himself, for his mouth craveth it of him.

00:59:06.395 --> 00:59:11.535
An ungodly man diggeth up evil, and in his lips there is a burning fire.

00:59:12.245 --> 00:59:18.315
A foward man soweth strife, and a whisperer separateth chief friends.

00:59:19.455 --> 00:59:25.635
A violent man enticeth his neighbor, and leadeth him into the way that is not good.

00:59:26.135 --> 00:59:32.155
He shutteth his eyes to devise foward things, moving his lips he bringeth evil to pass.

00:59:33.095 --> 00:59:38.275
The hoary head is a crown of glory, if it be found in the way of righteousness.

00:59:39.015 --> 00:59:42.435
He that is slow to anger is better than the mighty,

00:59:43.135 --> 00:59:47.295
and he that ruleth his spirit than he that taketh a city.

00:59:47.935 --> 00:59:52.895
The lot is cast into the lap, but the whole disposing thereof is of the Lord.

01:00:11.558 --> 01:00:19.798
Better is a dry morsel, and quietness therewith, than a house full of sacrifices with strife.

01:00:20.958 --> 01:00:26.838
A wise servant shall have rule over a son that causeth shame, and shall have part of

01:00:26.838 --> 01:00:28.498
the inheritance among the brethren.

01:00:29.038 --> 01:00:35.558
The finding pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold, but the Lord trieth the hearts.

01:00:36.778 --> 01:00:42.838
A wicked doer giveth heed to false lips, and a liar giveth ear to a naughty tongue.

01:00:43.838 --> 01:00:51.738
Whoso mocketh the poor reproacheth his Maker, and he that is glad at calamities shall not be unpunished.

01:00:52.678 --> 01:00:58.878
Children's children are the crown of old men, and the glory of children are their fathers.

01:00:59.478 --> 01:01:05.158
Excellent speech becomeeth not a fool, much less do lying lips a prince.

01:01:06.598 --> 01:01:11.578
A gift is as a precious stone in the eyes of him that hath it, whithersoever it turneth,

01:01:11.758 --> 01:01:18.918
it prospereth. He that covereth a transgression seeketh love, but he that repeateth a matter

01:01:18.918 --> 01:01:26.978
separeth very friends. A reprooth entereth more into a wise man than a hundred stripes into a fool.

01:01:27.818 --> 01:01:33.678
An evil man seeketh only rebellion, therefore a cruel messenger shall be sent against him.

01:01:34.958 --> 01:01:40.098
Let a bear robbed of her whelps meet a man rather than a fool in his folly.

01:01:40.898 --> 01:01:45.338
Whoso rewardeth evil for good, evil shall not depart from his house.

01:01:46.058 --> 01:01:52.898
The beginning of strife is as when one leadeth out water, therefore leave off contention before it be

01:01:52.898 --> 01:02:00.018
meddled with. He that justifieth the wicked, and he that condemneth the just, even they both are

01:02:00.018 --> 01:02:05.958
abomination to the Lord. Wherefore is there a price in the hand of a fool to get wisdom,

01:02:06.218 --> 01:02:14.278
seeing he hath no heart to it? A friend loveth at all times, and a brother is born for adversity.

01:02:15.338 --> 01:02:21.238
A man void of understanding striketh hands, and becomeeth surety in the presence of his friend.

01:02:22.058 --> 01:02:28.098
He loveth transgression that loveth strife, and he that exalteth his gait seeketh destruction.

01:02:29.778 --> 01:02:36.438
He that hath a foward heart findeth no good, and he that hath a perverse tongue falleth into mischief.

01:02:37.038 --> 01:02:42.738
He that begetteth a fool doeth it to his sorrow, and the father of a fool hath no joy.

01:02:43.378 --> 01:02:48.738
A merry heart doeth good like a medicine, but a broken spirit dryeth the bones.

01:02:49.818 --> 01:02:54.378
A wicked man taketh a gift out of the bosom to pervert the ways of judgment.

01:02:55.418 --> 01:03:01.038
Wisdom is before him that hath understanding, but the eyes of a fool are in the ends of the earth.

01:03:02.058 --> 01:03:08.758
A foolish son is a grief to his father, and bitterness to her that bear him. Also to punish

01:03:08.758 --> 01:03:16.298
the just is not good, nor to strike princes for equity. He that hath knowledge spareth his words,

01:03:16.818 --> 01:03:23.198
and a man of understanding is of an excellent spirit. Even a fool when he holdeth his peace

01:03:23.198 --> 01:03:28.998
is counted wise, and he that shutteth his lips is esteemed a man of understanding.

01:03:38.188 --> 01:03:39.368
18.

01:03:47.088 --> 01:03:53.508
Through desire a man, having separated himself, seeketh and intermedaleth with all wisdom.

01:03:54.888 --> 01:04:00.268
A fool hath no delight in understanding, but that his heart may discover itself.

01:04:01.448 --> 01:04:07.048
When the wicked cometh, then cometh also contempt, and with ignominy reproach.

01:04:07.048 --> 01:04:14.088
The words of a man's mouth are as deep waters, and the wellspring of wisdom as a flowing brook.

01:04:15.088 --> 01:04:19.788
It is not good to accept the person of the wicked to overthrow the righteous in judgment.

01:04:21.388 --> 01:04:26.388
A fool's lips enter into contention, and his mouth calleth for strokes.

01:04:27.888 --> 01:04:33.488
A fool's mouth is his destruction, and his lips are the snare of his soul.

01:04:34.728 --> 01:04:42.008
The words of a tale-bearer are as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.

01:04:42.868 --> 01:04:48.848
He also, that is slothful in his work, is brother to him that is a great waster.

01:04:49.328 --> 01:04:55.408
The name of the Lord is a strong tower, the righteous runneth into it, and is safe.

01:04:56.268 --> 01:05:02.648
The rich man's wealth is his strong city, and as in high wall in his own conceit.

01:05:02.648 --> 01:05:08.888
Before destruction the heart of a man is haughty, and before honor is humility.

01:05:10.148 --> 01:05:15.088
He that answereth a matter before he heareth it, it is folly and shame unto him.

01:05:15.708 --> 01:05:21.428
The spirit of a man will sustain his infirmity, but a wounded spirit who can bear?

01:05:22.828 --> 01:05:29.408
The heart of the prudent man geteth knowledge, and the ear of the wise seeketh knowledge.

01:05:29.408 --> 01:05:35.448
A man's gift maketh room for him, and bringeth him before great men.

01:05:36.528 --> 01:05:43.028
He that is first in his own cause seemeth just, but his neighbor cometh and searcheth him.

01:05:43.828 --> 01:05:49.068
The lot causeth contentions to cease, and parteth between the mighty.

01:05:49.888 --> 01:05:57.088
A brother offended is harder to be won than a strong city, and their contentions are like the bars of a castle.

01:05:59.048 --> 01:06:06.428
A man's belly shall be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth, and with the increase of his lips shall he be filled.

01:06:07.988 --> 01:06:14.388
Death and life are in the power of the tongue, and they that love it shall eat the fruit thereof.

01:06:14.968 --> 01:06:20.348
Whoso findeth a wife findeth a good thing, and obtaineth favor of the Lord.

01:06:20.988 --> 01:06:25.048
The poor useth in treaties, but the rich answereth roughly.

01:06:25.048 --> 01:06:32.888
A man that hath friends must show himself friendly, and there is a friend that sticketh closer than a brother.

01:06:52.233 --> 01:06:54.853
Better is the poor that walketh in his integrity,

01:06:55.633 --> 01:06:58.753
Than he that is perverse in his lips, and is a fool.

01:07:00.053 --> 01:07:03.833
Also that the soul be without knowledge, it is not good,

01:07:04.233 --> 01:07:06.733
And he that hasteth with his feet, sinneth.

01:07:07.393 --> 01:07:09.993
The foolishness of man perverteth his way,

01:07:09.993 --> 01:07:13.353
And his heart fredeth against the Lord.

01:07:13.733 --> 01:07:15.433
Wealth maketh many friends,

01:07:16.133 --> 01:07:18.653
But the poor is separated from his neighbor.

01:07:20.253 --> 01:07:22.953
A false witness shall not be unpunished,

01:07:23.473 --> 01:07:25.953
And he that speaketh lies shall not escape.

01:07:27.973 --> 01:07:30.493
Many will entreat the favor of the prince,

01:07:31.253 --> 01:07:34.093
And every man is a friend to him that giveth gifts.

01:07:35.653 --> 01:07:38.033
All the brethren of the poor do hate him,

01:07:38.033 --> 01:07:41.393
And how much more do his friends go far from him?

01:07:42.373 --> 01:07:45.833
He pursueth them with words, yet they are wanting to him.

01:07:46.773 --> 01:07:49.333
He that geteth wisdom loveth his own soul,

01:07:49.773 --> 01:07:52.453
He that keepeth understanding shall find good.

01:07:54.473 --> 01:07:56.893
A false witness shall not be unpunished,

01:07:57.453 --> 01:07:59.773
And he that speaketh lies shall perish.

01:08:01.753 --> 01:08:03.933
Delight is not seemly for a fool,

01:08:03.933 --> 01:08:07.213
Much less for a servant to have rule over princes.

01:08:08.193 --> 01:08:10.653
The discretion of a man differeth his anger,

01:08:11.513 --> 01:08:14.753
And it is his glory to pass over a transgression.

01:08:15.813 --> 01:08:18.393
The king's wrath is as the roaring of a lion,

01:08:19.373 --> 01:08:22.693
But his favor is as dew upon the grass.

01:08:23.733 --> 01:08:26.273
A foolish son is the calamity of his father,

01:08:27.053 --> 01:08:30.693
And the contentions of a wife are a continual dropping.

01:08:31.513 --> 01:08:34.873
House and riches are the inheritance of fathers,

01:08:35.413 --> 01:08:38.293
And a prudent wife is from the Lord.

01:08:39.033 --> 01:08:41.753
Slothfulness casteth into a deep sleep,

01:08:42.293 --> 01:08:44.693
And an idle soul shall suffer hunger.

01:08:45.413 --> 01:08:48.373
He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul,

01:08:49.313 --> 01:08:52.493
But he that despiseth his ways shall die.

01:08:53.193 --> 01:08:57.033
He that hath pity upon the poor lendeth unto the Lord,

01:08:57.033 --> 01:09:01.593
And that which he hath given will he pay him again.

01:09:03.293 --> 01:09:05.533
Chasen thy son while there is hope,

01:09:06.053 --> 01:09:08.873
And let not thy soul spare for his crying.

01:09:10.473 --> 01:09:13.113
A man of great wrath shall suffer punishment,

01:09:13.733 --> 01:09:17.233
For if thou deliver him, yet thou must do it again.

01:09:18.893 --> 01:09:21.613
Hear counsel, and receive instruction,

01:09:22.193 --> 01:09:25.313
That thou mayest be wise in thy latter end.

01:09:25.313 --> 01:09:28.833
There are many devices in a man's heart,

01:09:29.133 --> 01:09:32.373
Nevertheless the counsel of the Lord that shall stand.

01:09:33.253 --> 01:09:35.573
The desire of a man is his kindness,

01:09:36.453 --> 01:09:39.313
And a poor man is better than a liar.

01:09:40.573 --> 01:09:42.733
The fear of the Lord tendeth to life,

01:09:43.653 --> 01:09:46.513
And he that hath it shall abide satisfied.

01:09:47.433 --> 01:09:49.533
He shall not be visited with evil.

01:09:50.473 --> 01:09:53.853
A slothful man hideeth his hand in his bosom,

01:09:53.853 --> 01:09:57.653
And will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.

01:09:58.173 --> 01:10:01.273
Smite a scorner, and the simple will beware,

01:10:02.193 --> 01:10:04.213
And reprove one that hath understanding,

01:10:04.873 --> 01:10:06.493
And he will understand knowledge.

01:10:07.333 --> 01:10:11.453
He that wasteth his father, and chaseth away his mother,

01:10:11.993 --> 01:10:15.673
Is a son that causeth shame, and bringeth reproach.

01:10:16.593 --> 01:10:19.453
Cease, my son, to hear the instruction

01:10:19.453 --> 01:10:22.593
That causeth to err from the words of knowledge.

01:10:24.153 --> 01:10:26.493
An ungodly witness scorneth judgment,

01:10:27.333 --> 01:10:30.253
And the mouth of the wicked devoureth iniquity.

01:10:31.953 --> 01:10:34.253
Judgments are prepared for scorners,

01:10:34.573 --> 01:10:37.073
And stripes for the back of fools.

01:10:56.996 --> 01:10:58.756
Wine is a mocker,

01:10:59.176 --> 01:11:04.736
strong drink is raging, and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.

01:11:06.056 --> 01:11:09.576
The fear of a king is as the roaring of a lion,

01:11:10.076 --> 01:11:16.916
whoso provoketh him to anger, sinneth against his own soul. It is an honor for a man to cease from strife.

01:11:16.916 --> 01:11:22.996
But every fool will be meddling. The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold.

01:11:24.016 --> 01:11:26.756
Therefore shall he beg and harvest and have nothing.

01:11:28.376 --> 01:11:35.296
Council in the heart of man is like deep water, but a man of understanding will draw it out.

01:11:37.216 --> 01:11:43.096
Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness, but a faithful man who can find?

01:11:45.336 --> 01:11:50.496
The just man walketh in his integrity, his children are blessed after him.

01:11:52.476 --> 01:11:57.616
A king that sitteth in the throne of judgment scattereth away all evil with his eyes.

01:11:58.956 --> 01:12:03.796
Who can say I have made my heart clean? I am pure from my sin.

01:12:05.116 --> 01:12:11.456
Diverse weights and diverse measures, both of them are alike abomination to the Lord.

01:12:13.236 --> 01:12:19.496
Even a child is known by his doings, whether his work be pure and whether it be right.

01:12:20.336 --> 01:12:25.456
The hearing ear and the seeing eye, the Lord hath made even both of them.

01:12:26.816 --> 01:12:33.336
Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty, open thine eyes, and thou shalt be satisfied with bread.

01:12:34.536 --> 01:12:41.196
It is not, it is not, saith the buyer, but when he has gone his way, then he boasteth.

01:12:41.196 --> 01:12:47.836
There is gold and a multitude of rubies, but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.

01:12:48.696 --> 01:12:55.916
Take his garment, that is surety for a stranger, and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.

01:12:57.616 --> 01:13:03.456
Bread of deceit is sweet to a man, but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.

01:13:04.436 --> 01:13:09.296
Every purpose is established by council, and with good advice make war.

01:13:10.676 --> 01:13:18.476
He that goeth about is a tale-bearer, revealeth secrets, therefore meddle not with him that flattereth with his lips.

01:13:19.936 --> 01:13:25.696
Whoso curseth his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in obscure darkness.

01:13:26.996 --> 01:13:32.816
An inheritance may be gotten hastily at the beginning, but the end thereof shall not be blessed.

01:13:34.036 --> 01:13:40.566
Say not, thou, I will recompense evil, but wait on the Lord, and he shall save thee.

01:13:42.196 --> 01:13:48.236
Diverse waits are an abomination unto the Lord, and a false balance is not good.

01:13:50.276 --> 01:13:55.256
Man's goings are of the Lord. How can a man then understand his own way?

01:13:56.196 --> 01:14:02.956
It is a snare to the man who devoureth that which is holy, and after bows to make inquiry.

01:14:04.096 --> 01:14:08.916
A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth the wheel over them.

01:14:10.736 --> 01:14:17.396
The spirit of man is the candle of the Lord, searching all the inward parts of the belly.

01:14:19.296 --> 01:14:24.296
Mercy and truth preserve the king, and his throne is upholden by mercy.

01:14:25.256 --> 01:14:31.036
The glory of young men is their strength, and the beauty of old men is their gray head.

01:14:32.116 --> 01:14:37.936
The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil, so do stripes the inward parts of the belly.

01:14:48.431 --> 01:14:48.951
21.

01:14:56.631 --> 01:14:59.231
The King's heart is in the hand of the Lord.

01:14:59.611 --> 01:15:03.531
As the river is of water, he turneth it, whithersoever he will.

01:15:04.551 --> 01:15:09.851
Every way of a man is right in his own eyes, but the Lord pondereth the hearts.

01:15:10.731 --> 01:15:15.311
To do justice and judgment is more acceptable to the Lord than sacrifice.

01:15:16.191 --> 01:15:22.251
And high look, and a proud heart, and the ploughing of the wicked, is sin.

01:15:23.791 --> 01:15:27.351
The thoughts of the diligent tend only to plenteousness,

01:15:27.651 --> 01:15:30.611
but of every one that is hasty only to want.

01:15:32.251 --> 01:15:35.351
The getting of treasures by a lying tongue is a vanity,

01:15:35.791 --> 01:15:38.211
tossed to and fro of them that seek death.

01:15:40.371 --> 01:15:46.251
The robbery of the wicked shall destroy them, because they refuse to do judgment.

01:15:47.551 --> 01:15:53.931
The way of man is froward and strange, but as for the pure, his work is right.

01:15:55.071 --> 01:16:00.991
It is better to dwell in a corner of the housetop than with a brawling woman in a wide house.

01:16:02.191 --> 01:16:07.551
The soul of the wicked desireeth evil, his neighbour findeth no favour in his eyes.

01:16:08.811 --> 01:16:12.871
When the scornor is punished, the simple is made wise,

01:16:13.791 --> 01:16:17.191
and when the wise is instructed, he receiveth knowledge.

01:16:18.771 --> 01:16:22.071
The righteous man wisely considereth the house of the wicked,

01:16:22.911 --> 01:16:26.131
but God overthroweth the wicked for their wickedness.

01:16:27.451 --> 01:16:34.391
Whoso stoppeth his ears at the cry of the poor, he also shall cry himself, but shall not be heard.

01:16:36.991 --> 01:16:43.731
A gift in secret pacifieth anger, and a reward in the bosom, strong wrath.

01:16:44.671 --> 01:16:50.611
It is joy to the just to do judgment, but destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.

01:16:51.651 --> 01:16:58.031
A man that wandereth out of the way of understanding shall remain in the congregation of the dead.

01:16:59.351 --> 01:17:06.551
He that loveth pleasure shall be a poor man, he that loveth wine and oil shall not be rich.

01:17:08.491 --> 01:17:13.871
The wicked shall be a ransom for the righteous, and the transgressor for the upright.

01:17:15.231 --> 01:17:20.791
It is better to dwell in the wilderness than with a contentious and an angry woman.

01:17:21.611 --> 01:17:26.271
There is treasure to be desired, and oil in the dwelling of the wise,

01:17:26.271 --> 01:17:29.351
but a foolish man spendeth it up.

01:17:30.431 --> 01:17:36.511
He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life, righteousness, and honor.

01:17:37.891 --> 01:17:43.711
A wise man scaleth the city of the mighty, and casteth down the strength of the confidence thereof.

01:17:46.391 --> 01:17:50.931
Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles.

01:17:52.531 --> 01:17:56.251
Proud and haughty Scorner is his name who dealeth in proud wrath.

01:17:57.371 --> 01:18:02.931
The desire of the slothful killeth them, for his hands refuse to labor.

01:18:03.471 --> 01:18:08.771
He coveteth greedily all the day long, but the righteous giveth and spareth not.

01:18:10.191 --> 01:18:12.651
The sacrifice of the wicked is abomination.

01:18:13.351 --> 01:18:16.671
How much more when he bringeth it with a wicked mind?

01:18:17.651 --> 01:18:21.871
A false witness shall perish, but the man that heareth speaketh constantly.

01:18:22.991 --> 01:18:29.911
A wicked man hardeneth his face, but as for the upright he directeth his way.

01:18:30.811 --> 01:18:35.071
There is no wisdom, nor understanding, nor counsel against the Lord.

01:18:35.851 --> 01:18:41.251
The horse is prepared against the day of battle, but safety is of the Lord.

01:19:01.863 --> 01:19:05.523
A good name is rather to be chosen than great riches,

01:19:06.383 --> 01:19:09.763
And loving favor rather than silver and gold.

01:19:11.163 --> 01:19:16.123
The rich and poor meet together, The Lord is the maker of them all.

01:19:16.923 --> 01:19:21.883
A prudent man foreseeeth the evil, And hideeth himself,

01:19:22.783 --> 01:19:25.163
But the simple pass on and are punished.

01:19:26.183 --> 01:19:30.763
By humility and the fear of the Lord Are riches and honor and life.

01:19:32.923 --> 01:19:36.503
Thorns and snares are in the way of the froward,

01:19:37.463 --> 01:19:41.323
He that doth keep his soul shall be far from them.

01:19:43.083 --> 01:19:49.083
Train up a child in the way he should go, And when he is old he will not depart from it.

01:19:50.923 --> 01:19:56.583
The rich ruleth over the poor, And the borrower is servant to the lender.

01:19:58.643 --> 01:20:04.163
He that soweth iniquity shall reap vanity, And the rod of his anger shall fail.

01:20:05.603 --> 01:20:11.303
He that hath a bountiful eye shall be blessed, For he giveth of his bread to the poor,

01:20:13.583 --> 01:20:17.243
Cast out the scornor, and contention shall go out,

01:20:17.383 --> 01:20:19.763
Yea strife and reproach shall cease.

01:20:21.003 --> 01:20:26.423
He that loveth pureness of heart, For the grace of his lips the king shall be his friend.

01:20:28.223 --> 01:20:34.343
The eyes of the Lord preserve knowledge, And he overthroweth the words of the transgressor.

01:20:35.783 --> 01:20:41.143
The slothful man saith, There is a lion without, I shall be slain in the streets.

01:20:41.763 --> 01:20:48.763
The mouth of strange women is a deep pit, He that is abhorred of the Lord shall fall therein.

01:20:51.103 --> 01:20:56.903
Foolishness is bound in the heart of a child, But the rod of correction shall drive it far from him.

01:20:58.863 --> 01:21:01.863
He that oppresseth the poor to increase his riches,

01:21:02.323 --> 01:21:06.103
And he that giveth to the rich shall surely come to want.

01:21:07.463 --> 01:21:14.303
Bow down thine ear, and hear the words of the wise, And apply thine heart unto my knowledge.

01:21:15.123 --> 01:21:18.203
For it is a pleasant thing if thou keep them within thee,

01:21:18.663 --> 01:21:23.903
They shall withal be fitted in thy lips, That thy trust may be in the Lord.

01:21:24.323 --> 01:21:27.083
I have made known to thee this day even to thee.

01:21:27.683 --> 01:21:31.423
Have not I written to thee excellent things in counsels and knowledge,

01:21:31.983 --> 01:21:35.603
That I might make thee know the certainty of the words of truth?

01:21:35.603 --> 01:21:40.323
That thou mightest answer the words of truth to them that send unto thee.

01:21:42.323 --> 01:21:47.643
Rob not the poor, because he is poor, Neither oppress the afflicted in the gate,

01:21:47.923 --> 01:21:53.563
For the Lord will plead their cause, And spoil the soul of those that spoil them.

01:21:55.463 --> 01:22:00.483
Make no friendship with an angry man, And with a furious man thou shalt not go,

01:22:01.223 --> 01:22:04.983
Lest thou learn his ways, and get a snare to thy soul.

01:22:04.983 --> 01:22:11.423
Be not thou one of them that strike hands, Or of them that are sureties for debts.

01:22:12.063 --> 01:22:16.923
If thou hast nothing to pay, why should he take away thy bed from under thee?

01:22:17.923 --> 01:22:21.563
Remove not the ancient landmark which thy fathers have set.

01:22:22.923 --> 01:22:27.583
Seest thou a man diligent in his business? He shall stand before kings,

01:22:27.763 --> 01:22:30.223
He shall not stand before mean men.

01:22:49.286 --> 01:22:55.206
When thou sittest to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what is before thee, and put a

01:22:55.206 --> 01:22:58.686
knife to thy throat if thou be a man given to appetite.

01:22:59.686 --> 01:23:04.466
Be not desirous of his dainties, for they are deceitful meat.

01:23:05.106 --> 01:23:09.626
Labor not to be rich, cease from thine own wisdom.

01:23:10.346 --> 01:23:13.406
Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not?

01:23:13.806 --> 01:23:18.946
For riches certainly make themselves wings, they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.

01:23:20.166 --> 01:23:25.966
Eat thou not the bread of him that hath an evil eye, neither desire thou his dainty meats.

01:23:26.606 --> 01:23:29.486
For as he thinketh in his heart, so is he.

01:23:29.966 --> 01:23:33.786
Eat and drink, saith he to thee, but his heart is not with thee.

01:23:34.246 --> 01:23:39.226
The morsel which thou hast eaten, shalt thou vomit up and lose thy sweet words.

01:23:40.526 --> 01:23:46.126
Speak not in the ears of a fool, for he will despise the wisdom of thy words.

01:23:46.926 --> 01:23:52.066
Remove not the old landmark, and enter not into the fields of the fatherless.

01:23:52.726 --> 01:23:56.786
For their redeemer is mighty, he shall plead their cause with thee.

01:23:57.486 --> 01:24:01.726
Apply thine heart unto instruction and thine ears to the words of knowledge.

01:24:01.726 --> 01:24:08.006
Withhold not correction from the child, for if thou beatest him with the rod, he shall not die.

01:24:09.126 --> 01:24:14.146
Thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from hell.

01:24:15.046 --> 01:24:21.146
My son, if thine heart be wise, my heart shall rejoice, even mine.

01:24:21.706 --> 01:24:25.446
Yea, my reins shall rejoice when thy lips speak right things.

01:24:26.006 --> 01:24:32.126
Let not thine heart envy sinners, but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day long,

01:24:32.386 --> 01:24:37.546
for surely there is an end, and thine expectation shall not be cut off.

01:24:38.386 --> 01:24:43.086
Hear thou, my son, and be wise, and guide thine heart in the way.

01:24:43.706 --> 01:24:48.566
Be not among wine-bibbers, among riotous eaters of flesh,

01:24:49.186 --> 01:24:51.986
for the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty,

01:24:51.986 --> 01:24:56.446
and drowsiness shall clothe a man with rags.

01:24:57.486 --> 01:25:02.786
Harken unto thy father that begat thee, and despise not thy mother when she is old.

01:25:03.566 --> 01:25:08.026
Buy the truth and sell it not, also wisdom and instruction and understanding.

01:25:09.506 --> 01:25:12.626
The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice,

01:25:13.126 --> 01:25:17.106
and he that begetteth a wise child shall have joy of him.

01:25:17.926 --> 01:25:23.886
Thy father and thy mother shall be glad, and she that bear thee shall rejoice.

01:25:24.946 --> 01:25:30.806
My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways,

01:25:31.426 --> 01:25:36.146
for a whore is a deep ditch, and a strange woman is a narrow pit.

01:25:37.046 --> 01:25:42.866
She also lieth in wait as for a prey, and increaseth the transgressors among men.

01:25:43.506 --> 01:25:49.326
Who hath woe? Who hath sorrow? Who hath contentions? Who hath babbling?

01:25:49.846 --> 01:25:54.526
Who hath wounds without cause? Who hath redness of eyes?

01:25:55.366 --> 01:26:00.526
They that tarry long at the wine, They that go to seek mixed wine.

01:26:01.946 --> 01:26:04.486
Look not thou upon the wine when it is red,

01:26:05.046 --> 01:26:09.606
When it giveth its color in the cup, When it moveth itself aright.

01:26:10.486 --> 01:26:15.006
At the last it biteth like a serpent, And stingeth like an adder.

01:26:16.846 --> 01:26:21.526
Thine eyes shall behold strange women, And thine heart shall utter perverse things.

01:26:22.446 --> 01:26:26.706
Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down in the midst of the sea,

01:26:27.466 --> 01:26:33.586
Or as he that lieth upon the top of a mast. They have stricken me, shalt thou say,

01:26:33.786 --> 01:26:38.606
And I was not sick, they have beaten me, And I felt it not.

01:26:38.606 --> 01:26:42.366
When shall I awake? I will seek it yet again.

01:26:52.918 --> 01:26:53.958
24.

01:27:01.658 --> 01:27:09.198
Be not thou envious against evil men, neither desire to be with them, for their hearts studyeth

01:27:09.198 --> 01:27:13.198
destruction, and their lips talk of mischief.

01:27:13.818 --> 01:27:21.718
Through wisdom is an house builded, and by understanding it is established, and by knowledge

01:27:21.718 --> 01:27:25.718
shall the chambers be filled with all precious and pleasant riches.

01:27:26.838 --> 01:27:31.578
A wise man is strong, yea, a man of knowledge increaseth strength.

01:27:32.878 --> 01:27:39.238
For by wise counsel thou shalt make thy war, and in multitude of counsellors there is safety.

01:27:40.438 --> 01:27:45.238
Wisdom is too high for a fool, he openeth not his mouth in the gate.

01:27:45.898 --> 01:27:50.798
He that diviseth to do evil shall be called a mischievous person.

01:27:51.818 --> 01:27:58.238
The thought of foolishness is sin, and the scornor is an abomination to men.

01:27:59.358 --> 01:28:03.338
If thou faint in the day of adversity, thy strength is small.

01:28:05.198 --> 01:28:11.738
If thou forbear to deliver them that are drawn unto death, and those that are ready to be slain,

01:28:12.038 --> 01:28:17.658
if thou sayest, Behold, we knew it not, doth not he that pondereth the heart consider it?

01:28:17.658 --> 01:28:21.998
And he that keepeth thy soul, doth not he know it,

01:28:22.218 --> 01:28:26.018
and shall not he render to every man according to his works?

01:28:26.858 --> 01:28:33.638
My son, eat thou honey because it is good, and the honeycomb which is sweet to thy taste.

01:28:34.498 --> 01:28:37.498
So shall the knowledge of wisdom be unto thy soul.

01:28:38.038 --> 01:28:44.598
When thou hast found it, then there shall be a reward, and thy expectation shall not be cut off.

01:28:45.258 --> 01:28:49.838
Lay not wait, O wicked man, against the dwelling of the righteous.

01:28:50.398 --> 01:28:56.598
Spoil not his resting place, for a just man falleth seven times and riseth up again,

01:28:56.998 --> 01:29:03.518
but the wicked shall fall into mischief. Rejoice not when thine enemy falleth,

01:29:04.218 --> 01:29:10.498
and let not thine heart be glad when he stumbleeth, lest the Lord see it and it displease him,

01:29:10.498 --> 01:29:16.298
and he turn away his wrath from him. Fret not thyself because of evil men,

01:29:16.878 --> 01:29:22.358
neither be thou envious at the wicked, for there shall be no reward to the evil man.

01:29:22.958 --> 01:29:29.178
The candle of the wicked shall be put out. My son, fear thou the Lord and the King,

01:29:29.338 --> 01:29:36.338
and meddle not with them that are given to change, for their calamity shall rise suddenly,

01:29:36.898 --> 01:29:43.258
and who knoweth the ruin of them both? These things also belong to the wise.

01:29:44.138 --> 01:29:49.858
It is not good to have respect of persons in judgment. He that saith unto the wicked,

01:29:50.218 --> 01:29:58.178
thou are righteous, him shall the people curse, nations shall abhor him, but to them that rebuke

01:29:58.178 --> 01:30:04.738
him shall be delight, and a good blessing shall come upon them. Every man shall kiss his lips that

01:30:04.738 --> 01:30:11.078
giveeth a right answer. Prepare thy work without, and make it fit for thyself in the field,

01:30:11.918 --> 01:30:18.498
and afterwards build thine house. Be not a witness against thy neighbor without cause,

01:30:19.238 --> 01:30:25.718
and deceive not with thy lips. Say not I will do so to him as he hath done to me.

01:30:26.118 --> 01:30:31.578
I will render to the man according to his work. I went by the field of the slothful,

01:30:32.198 --> 01:30:38.158
and by the vineyard of the man void of understanding, and lo, it was all grown over

01:30:38.158 --> 01:30:44.158
with thorns, and nettles had covered the face thereof, and the stone wall thereof was broken

01:30:44.158 --> 01:30:51.098
down. Then I saw, and considered it well, I looked upon it, and received instruction.

01:30:51.998 --> 01:30:57.918
Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep.

01:30:57.918 --> 01:31:05.678
So shall thy poverty come as one that travaileth, and thy want as an armed man.

01:31:25.754 --> 01:31:31.494
These are the Proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah, king of Judah, copied out.

01:31:32.354 --> 01:31:39.114
It is the glory of God to conceal a thing, but the honor of kings is to search out a

01:31:39.114 --> 01:31:39.434
matter.

01:31:40.334 --> 01:31:46.194
The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings, is unsearchable.

01:31:47.014 --> 01:31:52.734
Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.

01:31:53.334 --> 01:31:59.034
Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.

01:32:01.094 --> 01:32:06.234
Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great

01:32:06.234 --> 01:32:06.674
men.

01:32:07.194 --> 01:32:12.554
For better it is that it be said unto thee, Come up hither, and that thou shouldest be

01:32:12.554 --> 01:32:16.434
put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.

01:32:17.214 --> 01:32:23.814
Go not forth hastily to strive, lest thou know not what to do in the end thereof, when

01:32:23.814 --> 01:32:26.134
thy neighbor hath put thee to shame.

01:32:27.034 --> 01:32:33.434
Debate thy cause with thy neighbor himself, and discover not a secret to another, lest

01:32:33.434 --> 01:32:37.814
he that heareth it put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.

01:32:39.234 --> 01:32:44.854
A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver.

01:32:45.554 --> 01:32:53.954
As an earring of gold in an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient

01:32:53.954 --> 01:32:54.534
ear.

01:32:55.434 --> 01:33:01.614
As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send

01:33:02.434 --> 01:33:05.274
for he refresheth the soul of his masters.

01:33:06.154 --> 01:33:13.234
Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift is like clouds and wind without rain.

01:33:14.014 --> 01:33:20.014
By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.

01:33:20.914 --> 01:33:22.434
Hast thou found honey?

01:33:22.834 --> 01:33:28.054
Eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith and vomit it.

01:33:29.374 --> 01:33:35.314
Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbor's house, lest he be weary of thee and so hate thee.

01:33:36.394 --> 01:33:42.594
A man that beareth false witness against his neighbor is a maul and a sword and a sharp

01:33:42.594 --> 01:33:43.194
arrow.

01:33:44.234 --> 01:33:50.074
Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth and a foot

01:33:50.074 --> 01:33:51.014
out of joint.

01:33:51.814 --> 01:33:59.854
As he that taketh away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon nitra, so is he that singeth

01:33:59.854 --> 01:34:01.694
songs to an heavy heart.

01:34:03.414 --> 01:34:09.394
If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat, and if he be thirsty, give him water

01:34:09.394 --> 01:34:16.114
to drink, for thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee.

01:34:16.534 --> 01:34:22.494
The north wind driveth away rain, so doth an angry countenance a backbiting tongue.

01:34:23.214 --> 01:34:29.274
It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop than with a brawling woman and in

01:34:29.274 --> 01:34:30.494
a wide house.

01:34:32.554 --> 01:34:38.594
As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.

01:34:39.634 --> 01:34:46.814
A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain and a corrupt spring.

01:34:47.774 --> 01:34:53.474
It is not good to eat much honey, so for men to search their own glory is not glory.

01:34:54.294 --> 01:35:00.654
He that hath no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down and without

01:35:00.654 --> 01:35:01.454
walls.

01:35:21.604 --> 01:35:27.944
As snow and summer, and as rain and harvest, So honour is not seemly for a fool.

01:35:28.784 --> 01:35:32.104
As the bird by wandering, as the swallow by flying,

01:35:32.944 --> 01:35:35.324
So the curse, causeless, shall not come.

01:35:36.044 --> 01:35:43.004
A whip for the horse, a bridle for the ass, And a rod for the fool's back.

01:35:44.184 --> 01:35:48.944
Answer not a fool according to his folly, Lest thou also be like unto him.

01:35:50.064 --> 01:35:55.324
Answer a fool according to his folly, Lest he be wise in his own conceit.

01:35:56.184 --> 01:36:02.224
He that sendeth a message by the hand of a fool, Cutteth off the feet, and drinketh damage.

01:36:03.004 --> 01:36:08.484
The legs of the lame are not equal, So is a parable in the mouth of fools.

01:36:11.024 --> 01:36:16.784
As he that bindeth a stone in a sling, So is he that giveth honour to a fool.

01:36:18.504 --> 01:36:25.244
As a thorn goeth up into the hand of a drunkard, So is a parable in the mouths of fools.

01:36:26.204 --> 01:36:32.944
The great God that formed all things both rewardeth the fool, And rewardeth transgressors.

01:36:33.704 --> 01:36:39.444
As a dog returneth to his vomit, So a fool returneth to his folly.

01:36:40.184 --> 01:36:47.644
Seest thou a man wise in his own conceit? There is more hope of a fool than of him.

01:36:48.724 --> 01:36:54.424
The slothful man saith, There is a lion in the way, A lion is in the streets.

01:36:55.944 --> 01:37:01.404
As the door turneth upon his hinges, So death the slothful upon his bed.

01:37:02.884 --> 01:37:09.124
The slothful hideeth his hand in his bosom, It grieveth him to bring it up again to his mouth.

01:37:10.064 --> 01:37:15.984
The sluggard is wiser in his own conceit Than seven men that can render a reason.

01:37:15.984 --> 01:37:21.424
He that passeth by, And medalleth with strife belonging not to him,

01:37:21.804 --> 01:37:25.064
Is like one that taketh a dog by the ears.

01:37:26.344 --> 01:37:30.444
As a mad man who casteth firebrands, arrows, and death,

01:37:31.104 --> 01:37:36.744
So is the man that deceiveth his neighbour, And saith, Am not I in sport?

01:37:37.844 --> 01:37:45.084
Where no wood is, there the fire goeth out. So, where there is no tale-bearer, the strife ceaseth.

01:37:46.124 --> 01:37:55.104
As coals are to burning coals, and wood to fire, So is a contentious man to kindle strife.

01:37:55.684 --> 01:38:03.884
The words of a tale-bearer are as wounds, And they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.

01:38:05.684 --> 01:38:12.004
Burning lips and a wicked heart Are like a potsherd covered with silver dross.

01:38:12.684 --> 01:38:18.684
He that hateth, dissembleth with his lips, And layeth up deceit within him.

01:38:19.624 --> 01:38:25.384
When he speaketh fair, believe him not, For there are seven abominations in his heart.

01:38:26.544 --> 01:38:32.064
Whose hatred is covered by deceit, His wickedness shall be shewed before the whole congregation.

01:38:33.524 --> 01:38:40.424
Whoso diggeth a pit shall fall therein, And he that rolleth a stone, it will return upon him.

01:38:40.424 --> 01:38:47.624
A lying tongue hateth those that are afflicted by it, And a flattering mouth worketh ruin.

01:39:07.660 --> 01:39:13.610
BOST NOT THYSELF OF TOMORROW, FOR THOU KNOWEST NOT WHAT A DAY MAY BRING FORTH.

01:39:14.410 --> 01:39:20.430
Let another man praise thee, and not thine own mouth, A stranger, and not thine own lips.

01:39:21.950 --> 01:39:28.920
A stone is heavy, and the sand weighty, But a fool's wrath is heavier than them both.

01:39:30.990 --> 01:39:37.770
Wrath is cruel, and anger is outrageous, But who is able to stand before envy?

01:39:39.730 --> 01:39:45.950
Open rebuke is better than secret love. Faithful are the wounds of a friend,

01:39:45.950 --> 01:39:53.870
But the kisses of an enemy are deceitful. The full soul loatheth in honeycomb,

01:39:55.150 --> 01:39:58.770
But to the hungry soul every bitter thing is sweet.

01:40:00.030 --> 01:40:05.350
As a bird that wandereth from her nest, So is a man that wandereth from his place.

01:40:07.430 --> 01:40:13.430
Ointment and perfume rejoice the heart, So doth the sweetness of a man's friend by

01:40:16.170 --> 01:40:20.690
Thy known friend, and thy father's friend forsake not,

01:40:21.690 --> 01:40:25.010
Neither go into thy brother's house in the day of thy calamity,

01:40:25.290 --> 01:40:29.110
For better is a neighbor that is near than a brother far off.

01:40:30.070 --> 01:40:37.950
My son, be wise, and make my heart glad, That I may answer him that reproacheth me.

01:40:39.290 --> 01:40:43.190
A prudent man foreseeeth the evil and hideeth himself,

01:40:43.870 --> 01:40:46.090
But the simple pass on and are punished.

01:40:48.190 --> 01:40:54.450
Take his garment that is surety for a stranger, And take a pledge of him for a strange woman.

01:40:55.950 --> 01:40:59.810
He that blesseth a friend with a loud voice rising early in the morning,

01:41:00.110 --> 01:41:06.730
It shall be counted a curse to him. A continual dropping in a very rainy day,

01:41:06.730 --> 01:41:12.270
And a contentious woman are alike. Whosoever hideeth her hideeth the wind,

01:41:12.970 --> 01:41:16.950
And the ointment of his right hand which bereth itself.

01:41:18.670 --> 01:41:24.190
Iron sharpeneth iron, so a man sharpeneth the countenance of his friend.

01:41:25.590 --> 01:41:28.890
Whoso keepeth the fig tree shall eat the fruit thereof,

01:41:29.510 --> 01:41:33.130
So he that waiteth on his master shall be honored.

01:41:35.550 --> 01:41:40.650
As in water face answereth to face, so the heart of man to man.

01:41:42.430 --> 01:41:47.830
Hell and destruction are never full, so the eyes of man are never satisfied.

01:41:49.810 --> 01:41:53.670
As the finding pot for silver, and the furnace for gold,

01:41:53.990 --> 01:41:55.970
So is a man to his praise.

01:41:56.990 --> 01:42:01.530
Though thou shouldest bray a fool in a mortar among wheat with a pestle,

01:42:01.530 --> 01:42:05.190
Yet will not his foolishness depart from him.

01:42:05.990 --> 01:42:08.870
Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks,

01:42:09.110 --> 01:42:12.870
And look well to thy herds, for riches are not forever.

01:42:13.630 --> 01:42:16.130
And doth the crown endure to every generation?

01:42:17.050 --> 01:42:20.710
The hay appearth, and the tender grass showeth itself,

01:42:21.250 --> 01:42:23.330
And the herbs of the mountains are gathered,

01:42:23.730 --> 01:42:28.490
The lambs are for thy clothing, and the goats are the price of the field.

01:42:29.270 --> 01:42:32.330
And thou shalt have goat's milk enough for thy food,

01:42:33.090 --> 01:42:37.710
For the food of thy household, and for the maintenance of thy maidens.

01:42:57.377 --> 01:43:02.997
The wicked flee when no man pursueth, But the righteous are bold as a lion.

01:43:04.017 --> 01:43:07.517
For the transgression of a land many are the princes thereof,

01:43:08.177 --> 01:43:13.717
But by a man of understanding and knowledge The state thereof shall be prolonged.

01:43:14.697 --> 01:43:21.087
A poor man that oppresseth the poor Is like a sweeping rain which leaveeth no food.

01:43:23.097 --> 01:43:28.647
They that forsake the law praise the wicked, But such as keep the law contend with them.

01:43:30.737 --> 01:43:36.647
Evil men understand not judgment, But they that seek the Lord understand all things.

01:43:38.127 --> 01:43:44.367
Better is the poor that walketh in his uprightness, That he that is perverse in his ways,

01:43:44.487 --> 01:43:45.667
Though he be rich.

01:43:46.927 --> 01:43:53.027
Whoso keepeth the law is a wise son, But he that is a companion of riotous men

01:43:53.027 --> 01:43:54.287
Shameth his father.

01:43:55.367 --> 01:43:58.967
He that by usury and unjust gain Increaseth his substance,

01:43:59.427 --> 01:44:02.167
He shall gather it for him that will pity the poor.

01:44:03.607 --> 01:44:09.587
He that turneth away his ear from hearing the law, Even his prayer shall be an abomination.

01:44:12.187 --> 01:44:15.827
Whoso causeth the righteous to go astray in an evil way,

01:44:16.227 --> 01:44:22.407
He shall fall himself into his own pit, But the upright shall have good things in possession.

01:44:23.927 --> 01:44:30.907
The rich man is wise in his own conceit, But the poor that hath understanding searcheth him out.

01:44:31.667 --> 01:44:39.407
When righteous men do rejoice there is great glory, But when the wicked rise a man is hidden.

01:44:42.107 --> 01:44:48.807
He that covereth his sins shall not prosper, But whoso confesseth and forsaketh them shall

01:44:48.807 --> 01:44:49.727
have mercy.

01:44:50.607 --> 01:44:58.287
Happy is the man that feareth all way, But he that hardeneth his heart shall fall into mischief.

01:44:59.307 --> 01:45:07.007
As a roaring lion and a raging bear, So is a wicked ruler over the poor people.

01:45:08.227 --> 01:45:12.607
The prince that wanteth understanding is also a great oppressor,

01:45:12.907 --> 01:45:17.147
But he that hateth covetousness shall prolong his days.

01:45:19.227 --> 01:45:23.747
A man that doeth violence to the blood of any person shall flee to the pit,

01:45:24.287 --> 01:45:25.647
Let no man stay him.

01:45:26.967 --> 01:45:34.507
Whoso walketh uprightly shall be saved, But he that is perverse in his ways shall fall at once.

01:45:36.327 --> 01:45:39.447
He that tilleth his land shall have plenty of bread,

01:45:40.327 --> 01:45:45.267
But he that followeth after vain persons shall have poverty enough.

01:45:46.287 --> 01:45:53.767
A faithful man shall abound with blessings, But he that maketh haste to be rich shall not be innocent.

01:45:54.527 --> 01:46:02.707
To have respect of persons is not good, For for a piece of bread that man will transgress.

01:46:04.747 --> 01:46:11.967
He that hasteth to be rich hath an evil eye, And considereth not that poverty shall come upon him.

01:46:13.607 --> 01:46:19.807
He that rebuketh a man afterwards shall find more favor than he that flattereth with the tongue.

01:46:21.407 --> 01:46:25.907
Whoso robbeth his father or his mother and saith it is no transgression,

01:46:26.427 --> 01:46:29.747
The same is the companion of a destroyer.

01:46:31.047 --> 01:46:39.027
He that is of a proud heart stirreth up strife, But he that putteth his trust in the Lord shall be made fat.

01:46:41.367 --> 01:46:48.727
He that trusteth in his own heart is a fool, But whoso walketh wisely he shall be delivered.

01:46:50.027 --> 01:46:57.607
He that giveth unto the poor shall not lack, But he that hideeth his eyes shall have many a curse.

01:46:58.907 --> 01:47:05.427
When the wicked rise men hide themselves, But when they perish the righteous increase.

01:47:31.981 --> 01:47:36.221
When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice.

01:47:37.141 --> 01:47:40.741
But when the wicked beareth rule, the people mourn.

01:47:41.921 --> 01:47:45.061
Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father,

01:47:45.981 --> 01:47:50.181
but he that keepeth company with harlots spendeth his substance.

01:47:52.281 --> 01:47:55.221
The king by judgment establisheth the land,

01:47:55.481 --> 01:47:58.281
but he that receiveth gifts overthroweth it.

01:47:59.201 --> 01:48:03.681
A man that flattereth his neighbor spreadeth a net for his feet.

01:48:05.081 --> 01:48:08.681
In the transgression of an evil man there is a snare,

01:48:08.681 --> 01:48:11.581
but the righteous doth sing and rejoice.

01:48:12.281 --> 01:48:15.061
The righteous considereth the cause of the poor,

01:48:15.541 --> 01:48:18.061
but the wicked regardeth not to know it.

01:48:19.021 --> 01:48:24.541
Scornful men bring a city into a snare, but wise men turn away wrath.

01:48:26.001 --> 01:48:29.081
If a wise man contendeth with a foolish man,

01:48:29.581 --> 01:48:32.521
whether he rage or laugh there is no rest.

01:48:33.541 --> 01:48:38.101
The bloodthirsty hate the upright, but the just seek his soul.

01:48:38.941 --> 01:48:44.981
A fool uttereth all his mind, but a wise man keepeth it until afterwards.

01:48:46.521 --> 01:48:50.281
If a ruler harken to lies, all his servants are wicked.

01:48:51.621 --> 01:48:54.321
The poor and deceitful men meet together.

01:48:54.861 --> 01:48:57.641
The Lord lighteneth both their eyes.

01:48:59.061 --> 01:49:01.361
The king that faithfully judgeth the poor,

01:49:01.901 --> 01:49:04.081
his throne shall be established forever.

01:49:05.241 --> 01:49:08.061
The rod and reproof give wisdom.

01:49:08.681 --> 01:49:12.201
But a child left to himself bringeth his mother to shame.

01:49:13.861 --> 01:49:17.201
When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increaseth,

01:49:17.561 --> 01:49:19.781
but the righteous shall see their fall.

01:49:20.821 --> 01:49:23.861
Correct thy son, and he shall give thee rest,

01:49:24.101 --> 01:49:26.941
yea, he shall give delight unto thy soul.

01:49:28.741 --> 01:49:31.581
Where there is no vision, the people perish,

01:49:32.421 --> 01:49:34.921
but he that keepeth the law happy is he.

01:49:36.261 --> 01:49:39.261
A servant will not be corrected by words,

01:49:39.641 --> 01:49:42.361
for though he understand, he will not answer.

01:49:44.201 --> 01:49:46.761
Seest thou a man that is hasty in his words,

01:49:47.261 --> 01:49:49.641
there is more hope for a fool than for him.

01:49:49.921 --> 01:49:53.841
He that delicately bringeth up his servant from a child

01:49:53.841 --> 01:49:56.721
shall have him become his son at the length.

01:49:58.861 --> 01:50:01.501
An angry man stirreth up strife,

01:50:01.901 --> 01:50:04.901
and a furious man aboundeth in transgression.

01:50:06.481 --> 01:50:09.461
A man's pride shall bring him low,

01:50:10.201 --> 01:50:13.221
but honor shall uphold the humble in spirit.

01:50:14.561 --> 01:50:18.201
Whoso is partner with a thief, hateth his own soul.

01:50:18.901 --> 01:50:21.881
He heareth cursing, and berayeth it not.

01:50:23.741 --> 01:50:25.901
The fear of man bringeth a snare,

01:50:27.061 --> 01:50:30.461
but whoso putteth his trust in the Lord shall be safe.

01:50:31.761 --> 01:50:33.781
Many seek the ruler's favor,

01:50:34.461 --> 01:50:37.521
but every man's judgment cometh from the Lord.

01:50:38.721 --> 01:50:42.181
An unjust man is an abomination to the just,

01:50:43.221 --> 01:50:47.221
and he that is upright in the way is abomination to the wicked.

01:51:06.326 --> 01:51:15.126
The words of Agur, son of Jakesh, even the prophecy the man spake unto Ithiel, even unto

01:51:15.126 --> 01:51:16.366
Ithiel and Ucal.

01:51:17.926 --> 01:51:23.286
Surely I am more brutish than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.

01:51:23.766 --> 01:51:27.986
I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy.

01:51:29.166 --> 01:51:31.566
Who hath ascended up to heaven, or descended?

01:51:32.346 --> 01:51:35.126
Who hath gathered the wind in his fists?

01:51:35.886 --> 01:51:38.286
Who hath bound the waters in a garment?

01:51:38.886 --> 01:51:41.526
Who hath established all the ends of the earth?

01:51:42.326 --> 01:51:43.566
What is his name?

01:51:44.166 --> 01:51:47.066
And what is his son's name, if thou canst tell?

01:51:48.486 --> 01:51:50.206
Every word of God is pure.

01:51:50.206 --> 01:51:54.226
He is a shield unto them that put their trust in him.

01:51:54.866 --> 01:52:00.146
Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.

01:52:00.786 --> 01:52:02.906
Two things have I required of thee.

01:52:03.546 --> 01:52:05.706
Deny me them not before I die.

01:52:06.486 --> 01:52:09.186
Remove far from me vanity and lies.

01:52:09.806 --> 01:52:12.066
Give me neither poverty nor riches.

01:52:12.986 --> 01:52:20.186
Feed me with food convenient for me, lest I be full and deny thee, and say, Who is the

01:52:20.186 --> 01:52:20.606
Lord?

01:52:21.106 --> 01:52:25.446
Or lest I be poor and steal, and take the name of my God in vain?

01:52:27.926 --> 01:52:33.786
Accused not a servant unto his master, lest he curse thee, and thou be found guilty.

01:52:35.066 --> 01:52:39.426
There is a generation that curseth their father, and doth not bless their mother.

01:52:40.186 --> 01:52:46.306
There is a generation that are purer in their own eyes, and yet is not washed from their

01:52:46.306 --> 01:52:47.086
filthiness.

01:52:47.806 --> 01:52:54.506
There is a generation, O how lofty are their eyes, and their eyelids are lifted up.

01:52:55.306 --> 01:53:01.866
There is a generation whose teeth are as swords, and their jawed teeth as knives, to devour

01:53:01.866 --> 01:53:05.926
the poor from off the earth, and the needy from among men.

01:53:07.586 --> 01:53:11.926
The horse leech hath two daughters crying, Give, give.

01:53:13.066 --> 01:53:20.306
There are three things that are never satisfied, Yea, four things say not it is enough,

01:53:20.986 --> 01:53:26.546
The grave, and the barren womb, The earth that is not filled with water,

01:53:27.146 --> 01:53:29.706
And the fire that saith not it is enough.

01:53:30.506 --> 01:53:34.286
The eye that mocketh at his father, and despiseth to obey his mother,

01:53:34.406 --> 01:53:39.306
The ravens of the valley shall pick it out, And the young eagle shall eat it.

01:53:39.306 --> 01:53:45.006
There be three things which are too wonderful for me, Yea, four which I know not,

01:53:45.646 --> 01:53:50.266
The way of an eagle in the air, The way of a serpent upon a rock,

01:53:51.026 --> 01:53:56.266
The way of a ship in the midst of the sea, And the way of a man with a maid.

01:53:57.246 --> 01:54:01.566
Such is the way of an adulterous woman, She eateth, and wipeth her mouth,

01:54:01.686 --> 01:54:03.886
And saith, I have done no wickedness.

01:54:04.786 --> 01:54:10.506
For three things the earth is disquieted, And for four which it cannot bear,

01:54:11.286 --> 01:54:16.686
For a servant when he reigneth, And a fool when he is filled with meat,

01:54:17.326 --> 01:54:24.626
For an odious woman when she is married, And an handmaid that is heir to her mistress.

01:54:25.986 --> 01:54:30.766
There be four things which are little upon the earth, But they are exceeding wise.

01:54:31.446 --> 01:54:37.386
The ants are a people not strong, Yet they prepare their meat in the summer.

01:54:38.426 --> 01:54:43.626
The conies are but a feeble folk, Yet they make their houses in the rocks.

01:54:44.426 --> 01:54:49.486
The locusts have no king, Yet they go forth all of them by bands.

01:54:50.646 --> 01:54:55.466
The spider taketh hold in her hands, And is in king's palaces.

01:54:56.446 --> 01:55:01.666
There be three things which go well, Yea, four are comely in going.

01:55:02.866 --> 01:55:07.286
A lion which is strongest among beasts, And turneth not away for any,

01:55:07.786 --> 01:55:13.226
A greyhound, and he goat also, And a king against whom there is no rising up.

01:55:15.186 --> 01:55:20.826
If thou hast done foolishly in lifting up thyself, Or if thou hast thought evil,

01:55:21.506 --> 01:55:23.306
Lay thine hand upon thy mouth.

01:55:24.386 --> 01:55:27.426
Surely the churning of milk bringeth forth butter,

01:55:28.126 --> 01:55:34.276
And the ringing of the nose bringeth forth blood, So the forcing of wrath bringeth forth strife.

01:55:49.589 --> 01:55:52.349
THIS LIBERVOX RECORDING IS IN THE PUBLIC DOMAIN.

01:55:55.629 --> 01:55:57.569
THE WORDS OF KING LE MUEL.

01:55:58.309 --> 01:56:00.669
THE PROPHECY THAT HIS MOTHER TAUGHT HIM.

01:56:01.809 --> 01:56:08.469
What my son, and what the son of my womb, and what the son of my vows?

01:56:09.189 --> 01:56:15.189
Give not thy strength unto women, nor thy ways to that which destroyeth kings.

01:56:16.549 --> 01:56:24.469
It is not for kings, O le Muel, it is not for kings to drink wine, nor for princes strong drink,

01:56:25.689 --> 01:56:31.029
lest they drink and forget the law and pervert the judgment of any of the afflicted.

01:56:31.849 --> 01:56:39.509
Give strong drink unto him that is ready to perish, and wine unto those that be of heavy hearts,

01:56:39.909 --> 01:56:45.609
let him drink, and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more.

01:56:46.709 --> 01:56:51.689
Open thy mouth for the dumb and the cause of all such that are appointed to destruction.

01:56:52.949 --> 01:56:59.049
Open thy mouth, judge righteously, and plead the cause of the poor and needy.

01:57:00.069 --> 01:57:06.489
Who can find a virtuous woman? For her price is far above rubies.

01:57:07.249 --> 01:57:13.789
The heart of her husband doth safely trust in her, so that he shall have no need of spoil.

01:57:14.649 --> 01:57:19.389
She will do him good, and not evil all the days of her life.

01:57:20.349 --> 01:57:25.769
She seeketh wool and flax, and worketh willingly with her hands.

01:57:25.769 --> 01:57:31.289
She is like the merchant's ships. She bringeth her food from afar.

01:57:32.089 --> 01:57:39.149
She riseth also while it is yet night, and giveth meat to her household and a portion to her maidens.

01:57:40.129 --> 01:57:46.609
She considereth a field, and buyeth it. With the fruit of her hands she planteth a vineyard.

01:57:47.129 --> 01:57:51.609
She girdeth her loins with strength, and strengtheneth her arms.

01:57:51.609 --> 01:57:58.449
She perceiveth that her merchandise is good. Her candle goeth not out by night.

01:57:59.509 --> 01:58:03.749
She layeth her hands to the spindle, and her hands hold the distaff.

01:58:04.829 --> 01:58:10.649
She stretcheth out her hand to the poor, yea, she reacheth forth her hands to the needy.

01:58:11.409 --> 01:58:17.429
She is not afraid of the snow, for her household, for all her household, are clothed with scarlet.

01:58:18.449 --> 01:58:23.929
She maketh herself coverings of tapestry. Her clothing is silk and purple.

01:58:24.609 --> 01:58:29.629
Her husband is known in the gates, when he sitteth among the elders of the land.

01:58:31.089 --> 01:58:35.849
She maketh fine linen and selleth it, and delivereth girdles unto the merchant.

01:58:36.949 --> 01:58:41.969
Strength and honor are her clothing, and she shall rejoice in time to come.

01:58:42.479 --> 01:58:47.929
She openeth her mouth with wisdom, and in her tongue is the law of kindness.

01:58:48.609 --> 01:58:53.929
She looketh well to the ways of her household, and eateth not the bread of idleness.

01:58:54.729 --> 01:59:01.929
Her children arise up, and call her blessed. Her husband also, and he praiseth her.

01:59:02.849 --> 01:59:08.209
Many daughters have done virtuously, but thou excelest them all.

01:59:09.089 --> 01:59:16.549
Favor is deceitful, and beauty is vain, but a woman that feareth the Lord, she shall be praised.

01:59:17.569 --> 01:59:23.949
Give her of the fruit of her hands, and let her own works praise her in the gates.
